INSERT INTO `chapters` VALUES (1,'CHAPTER 1',1,1,'39e124e0464c11e9aff0f56449573457','39e124e0464c11e9aff0f56449573457','2019-01-03 10:23:02','2019-03-14 17:02:20','<p>Let us start very straight by focusing how important is our mind in our life and the life we live. Mind is just like our driver who drives us on its will. Try to control your mind for just 10 minutes and you will come to know how it struggles to focus on one particular agenda. So it is impossible to even understand what we will try to say in our subsequent videos till the time our mind is set to accept it. The reason being it is never tuned to understand those things. That is the reason the ARENA of ‘Mindset’ is very important to move forward and understand our teachings in a proper way.</p><p>Mind is the most powerful tool for human being. In most of the cases it is not tuned in a way to achieve financial abundance. So it is just like a driver who drives you without knowing where it has to take you. Try to understand if you are catching a cab and your driver is not informed where you want to go? Driver will keep you driving and driving because he is not aware of your destination. The same is the case with most of us. So the first step to go forward is to tune our mind to accept and understand a way forward.</p><p>Haven’t you heard phrases like:</p><p><strong><em>“Money grows on a tree or what?”</em></strong></p><p><strong><em>“Money is a root cause of all evils”?</em></strong></p><p><strong><em>“Money can’t buy you happiness?”</em></strong></p><p><strong><em>“We don’t have money to afford it”?</em></strong></p><p><strong><em>“Money can only be earned through hard work”?</em></strong></p><p><strong><em>“Money is not meant for us”?</em></strong></p><p>&amp; lot more</p><p>We have been hearing such phrases since childhood and what it has done?</p><p>It has turned &amp; convinced our subconscious mind that money is bad, difficult to earn, far away from us etc. And it has convinced our subconscious mind that not having money is good and keep finding reasons to convince ourselves why it is not good to have money. But deep inside our mind we still want it because of growing necessities. Our mind is deeply convinced that money is most difficult to earn.</p><p>But now our mind is conditioned in a very narrow way and the perception about money is at rock bottom. If mind is not convinced that money can’t be earned easily, do whatever you want or try as hard as you can, you will not be able to achieve financial abundance. <strong>So the first task for us is to recondition our mind in such a way that it should automatically start attracting wealth.</strong> That is the main difference between a person who is financially rich and un-wealthy person.</p><p>What if we ask to lift 100 kg weight to a physically weak person? He will not be able to lift it. Now the same weight if we ask a physically strong guy who got strength to lift 100 kgs, he will lift it easily. What is the main difference between physically weak guy and physically strong guy?</p><p>Answer is strength &amp; power.</p><p>Now there are 2 possibilities to lift 100 kg of weight</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Either the guy is naturally strong enough to lift 100 kg</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Or the guy works very hard, hit out gym everyday to gain strength and power to lift the weight.</p><p>Now the question is whether physically weak guy can ever lift 100 kg weight?</p><p>Answer is yes if he works very hard on his body to gather that strength and power.</p><p>The same is the case with wealth. Somebody got it by birth i.e. naturally and some has to work really hard to get it. Earlier we asked you what is the main difference between physically weak guy and physically strong guy to lift 100 kg of weight? Strength &amp; Power</p><p>Let us ask you what is the main difference between financially rich man who is wealthy and a poor &amp; unwealthy man?</p><p>The answer is <strong>MINDSET</strong></p>','90e6f34010d311e989ddb34e6863d087'),(2,'CHAPTER 2',1,2,'75a2c3c0464c11e9a2f79dacac76457c','75a2c3c0464c11e9a2f79dacac76457c','2019-01-03 10:24:31','2019-03-14 17:02:32','<p>Dictionary meaning of MINDSET is ‘a person’s way of thinking and their opinions’</p><p>Mindset of two individuals is never the same. Some is born with positive optimistic mindset whereas mindset of some people is narrower than thin thread. There are many factors because of which mindset develops and take shapes. The main factor which gives earlier shape to mindset is a family of an individual. As a child we are hardly scared of anything. The mindset was fearless. If a kid is asked to jump in fire, he will do it because he has never experienced that fire harms. But gradually as he grows up he starts developing mindset.</p><p>Here comes the turning point in future of an individual. Once kids starting growing up, they start cultivating mindset of their family. If the family is poor, mindset takes poor mode. If the family is rich, mindset takes rich mode. If the family takes risk, mindset of kid grows that way. If the mindset of family is conservative, mindset develops in conservative way. Mindset of an individual is replica of mindset of their family. In very rare cases mindset of an individual goes in other direction than mindset of their family. It also depends upon how people teach their kids.</p><p>Kids of poor has always seen their parents struggling for basic things, so their mindset starts believing that life is full of struggle. Eventually when they grow up they struggle because that is how their mindset is conditioned.</p><p>Even most of middle class families got struggling mindsets. They study hard to get good job. Than they work hard to earn money. Most of middle class families earn to take care of their expenditures. Though most of them are good dreamers but their mindset never supports to fulfill those dreams. And they keep struggling entire life to take care of expenditures of themselves and family. There kids develop same mindset – Study hard, work hard, struggle hard. Most of middle class people are scared of taking risks and they don’t allow their children to take risk. That is why most of middle class people always remain middle class</p><p>Now let’s come to rich class. Rich class people are rich because their mindset is rich. They got the mindset to rule across society. They don’t like small things. They believe that same amount of energy is required to do big things the amount which is required to do pity things, then why go for small? They got the mindset to utilize most of 86400 seconds available in a day &amp; don’t believe in wasting time. They know how to utilize small thinking of middle class and poor class people to get maximum benefits out of them. They want entire world to work for them. They read a lot, they learn a lot. They got big wide open mindset and that is how their kids inherit it from them. They always remain out of their comfort zone and do their activities.</p><p>So basically we live the size of our mindset. It is as simple as this.</p><p>Further mindset takes shape of environment we live in. Often we have seen rich people send their kids to rich school so that they get the environment required to develop mindset like them.</p><p>If rich kid is sent in a school meant for middle class people, there are two possibilities</p><ul><li><strong>Either he will not be able to adjust among kids or feel uncomfortable with surroundings</strong></li><li><strong>Or he will start cultivating middle class mindset</strong></li></ul><p>Now reverse the case</p><p>If middle class kid is sent in a school meant for rich class people, there are following possibilities</p><ul><li><strong>He will not be able to adjust among their lifestyle. He will start feeling complex and inferior. He may get depressed within months by seeing lifestyle of rich.</strong></li><li><strong>Or he will start cultivating mindset of Rich people.</strong></li></ul><p>So for a person following things are very important for framing his mindset:</p><ul><li><strong>Education he gets</strong></li><li><strong>School he goes to</strong></li><li><strong>Friend circle he is into</strong></li><li><strong>Approach towards life he has</strong></li><li><strong>Risk Taking ability</strong></li><li><strong>Sports he plays</strong></li><li><strong>Activities he does</strong></li><li><strong>Mindset of family he is born into</strong></li><li><strong>Approach towards other people</strong></li><li><strong>Ability to adopt changes</strong></li><li><strong>Willingness to learn</strong></li><li><strong>Lifestyle he is living</strong></li><li><strong>Lot of other things</strong></li></ul>','92a2b17010d311e981726121b3027a72'),(3,'CHAPTER 3',1,3,'9c17d700464c11e99c8ef749f3157d90','9c17d700464c11e99c8ef749f3157d90','2019-01-03 10:25:22','2019-03-14 17:02:47','<p>Now the most important thing – can mindset be changed?</p><p>Yes, it can be changed</p><p>How?</p><p>By consistently following or practicing things which rich &amp; successful people do, which can impact your subconscious mind.</p><p>Let’s start practicing following things which will surely turn your small mindset to the mindset which attracts lot of wealth and success. Let’s cover it one by one.</p><p>Here are few:</p><ul><li><strong>Set Your Mind to get set go –</strong></li></ul><p>We go through variety of stress in life. We go through lot and lot of problems. There is not even a single human being who doesn’t have any problems in life. Whatever we have covered till now and whatever we will cover in future will require your mind on place. Unless your mind is on place everything we talk about is just a piece of crap.</p><p>The most powerful thing available in human being is our MIND. Just try to control it for 20 minutes, it will run you on its tune. Nobody on earth can control his mind completely and its been said and proved that through meditation you can control it to some extent. Once you start controlling your mind, it will give you strength to control your emotions and thus your actions. Once your emotions are controlled, it will give you better idea and guidance to take proper actions. And our life is result of decisions and actions we take.</p><p>We talk about happiness; we talk about financial literacy or whatever we will talk about, will go much above your head if your mind is not set or your mind is not stable. And how can you assume your mind to be stable if you are in deep debt or you are facing some family crisis. We would not enjoy in teaching you if your mind is not stable and meditation is only medicine we can give to stabilize your mind, so that we can feed you with further input.</p><p><strong>MEDITATE FOR MINIMUM 10 MINUTES TO START WITH.</strong></p><p>Keep our words, it will change your life, your stress levels, your perception, your control, your belief, everything.</p><p>Moreover, we keep looking for happiness, abundance and positivity across the world. We do it through out our life. We tell you with conviction and you will start believing us once you start practicing meditation for a week that all the happiness of life, all the abundance of of life, all the positivity of life is available deep inside us. And to penetrate inside we have to meditate. It will not only take your stress, depression &amp; anxiety out but also gives you a direction in life. Meditation might give you your purpose in life. It is the most powerful tool available in human life.</p><p>Mind is our driver who drives us on its tune and it is important to give direction to our driver to reach some destination. But here mind is like a wild elephant who is out of control and can destroy environment around and to give it a direction first we have to control it. Meditation is the only solution to control this wild elephant before it accepts any of our order. So let’s start meditating so that we can control this wild driver and accepts our order to drop us to our destination of ‘Financial Abundance’</p>','945deea010d311e9a24adf2ed3599983'),(4,'CHAPTER 4',1,4,'1b183700466211e9bbd265f45e5c8969','1b183700466211e9bbd265f45e5c8969','2019-01-03 10:26:07','2019-03-14 19:37:10','<ul><li><strong>Change your mindset – Think big out of your imagination zone</strong></li></ul><p>Majority of middle class and poor class people have a mindset to earn only to take care of expenditures. How abundance could be achieved unless you target that. We are occupied in our routine monthly expenses so badly that our mind never gets out of it. So mind is stuck in that fixed monthly basic expenditure. Unless mind gets out of it, it is impossible to achieve money in abundance.</p><p>Rich people hardly have time to think of monthly household expenditures and rather think of some more sources to increase their wealth. No doubt budgeting is important and even rich has to think of arranging finances for XXX investment or replaying XXX loans but their mind is not stuck between to earn only to take care of expenditures. They always think of multiplication and abundance. They borrow money to make more out of it.</p><p>Mind is like a tank of water in your house. We expect water to be stored in a tank. If the size of tank is 10L we cannot expect to store 50L of water in that. In a same way, if size of our mind is small or fixed that we have to take care of our expenses, we just cannot earn more than the size of our expenses. It will not be possible for us to accumulate wealth. So it is very important to increase size of our mind and think big. Always think about earning in abundance. Get out of monthly household expenses and start thinking about how to earn 10 years of your house hold expenses in a month. Believe us, just like a size of tank, wealth has to fill as per size of your mind.&nbsp;</p><p>Let us tell you very honestly that it is not that easy the way we say. If your current situation is like it is getting difficult to earn even your basic monthly expenditure and we ask you to think in abundance, you will not be able to relate to it. But there are regular exercise or ways through which we can change our mindset and it will start thinking out of the box. It will take you out of your current financial situations and start thinking out of it.</p><p>Gradual and regular practice of following activities will help you achieve it:</p><ul><li><strong>Start your day with Positive Motivational Video of abundance – It will help to activate your subconscious mind to remain positive and take your mind in a way you want</strong></li><li><strong>End your day with positive Motivational video of abundance – Subconscious mind is super active during night sleep and whatever we do before sleep remains in deep roots of our subconscious mind. So if we end our day with some horror story, there are 90% chances you will have scary dreams. In a same way if you end your day with positive mind of abundance, it will spread positivity in deep roots of your subconscious mind.</strong></li><li><strong>Meditation –</strong></li></ul><p><strong>We have already suggested to start meditation which will help your mind from current financial and other struggles you are going through.</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Stay away from negative toxic people</strong></li></ul><p>Please understand, you can reach moon only if you target to reach stars. Same way, if you think big than only you will be able to achieve something big. In other words, big things come to only those who think big.</p><p>More importantly you will be surprised to know that same amount of efforts is required to do big things the amount which is required to do small things. So why waste time on small pity things.</p><p>Everybody on this earth gets only 1 life – it is up to us to die in poverty or leave a mark for this world. You know your situation better, if you can be example for whole world or die in some corner without anyone knowing our existence.&nbsp;</p>','9616c5c010d311e9a55643825457016a'),(5,'CHAPTER 5',1,5,'04ee14e0466311e9b020cf796705e154','04ee14e0466311e9b020cf796705e154','2019-01-03 10:27:02','2019-03-14 19:57:35','<ul><li>Step out of your comfort zone –</li></ul><p><strong style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\"><em>“If you do what you’ve always done, you’ll get what you’ve always gotten.”</em></strong></p><p><strong style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\"> ~ Tony Robbins</strong></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">Comfort Zone is defined as a situation where you feel completely secure, comfortable and relaxed to what you currently have. This is the state which highly successful people try their best to avoid. Because opposite to what common people believes that being in the comfort zone is safe, successful people on the other hand knows how dangerous it is when you are in your comfort zone.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">One prominent condition that holds many people back in life is the fear of leaving their comfort zone. What is this comfort zone thing all about? The scientific name for the comfort zone is the “Corley Syndrome,” and it is a type of mental conditioning that can cause a person to create, operate, and stay within certain mental boundaries.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\"> For many, this false sense of security eventually leads to complacency, inaction and people end up staying stuck within this place. Your comfort zone is potentially the greatest enemy of your achievement in life.&nbsp;</span></p><p>Its tendency of human being to do things or take up activities as per their comfort. We follow the same thing in making new friends, following people or making our network. We live in our comfort zone. We study what we are comfortable with. We eat what we are comfortable with. We listen what we are comfortable with. It is not a new thing but very dangerous if you remain in your comfort zone for your entire life. It starts with small routine like sleeping too late, wake up late, kill time, eat unhealthy and then it becomes habit. Be aware that it is very difficult to get out of habit. When there comes time to start your career and earn money, we find ourselves comfortable with habits which might not be good for your career.</p><p>For people who are already in business or working somewhere, they keep doing same things as per their comfort zone and than expect tomorrow to be better. Its very simple logic, if you are not happy with your today and want tomorrow to be better you have to change your activities you have been doing till today. It’s so simple and people take life span to understand this very simple basic logic. How can you expect orange juice to come as output when you insert carrot in your juicer as input?To expect better output, you have to work hard to change your inputs. You have to work smartly to change your activities if you are not happy with your today and change your tomorrow. So basically you have to get out of your comfort zone to improve your tomorrow. If you are happy with your current situation, that means you are doing activities which matches with your expected output. That also means you are already either out of your comfort zone or the activities you are comfortable with matches with the outcome you expect in your life.</p><p>So, if you are not comfortable in meeting new people – go out and meet maximum number of people. Take a target to meet xxx number of people daily.</p><p>If you are not comfortable in accounts – Go out and join some good accounting classes today</p><p>If you are not comfortable in public speaking – take deliberate effort to join some personality development course where you get to speak in public</p><p>If you are not comfortable talking about your business to new prospects – join some business network community where you have to compulsorily discuss about your business with strangers</p><p>We have seen people are scared to discuss their financial situation if they are in financial trouble or in huge debt – Please get out of your comfort zone, speak to some good lawyer who will either help you to declare bankruptcy or speak to good advisor who might help you to get out of it. If not, speak to people about your situation so that if somebody can help you to get out of it by either taking you out of it or help in some or the other way. But you have to get out of your comfort zone. It is very much possible that your current financial situation is because of your activities you are doing currently as per your comfort zone. Like if you are in business and your business requires your involvement to boost up your team during morning, but you are comfortable to start your day by noon and the business is affected. It requires you to get out of your comfort zone and reach office before your team arrives.</p><p>It is possible that your business requires your attention on sales and you are not comfortable with sales – than its high time to learn sales techniques and start focusing on your sales.</p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">Inability to get out of comfort zone has chain negative effects. The first effect you will feel is the lack of progress in your life. Next, lack of progress gives a lot of spaces for hardship. When you experience hardship, then you will feel bored or discontented in your life. You might constantly feel burdened by life. Hope you can answer why. You are right, being comfortable is often the reason for discontentment, because you did not let progress come into your doors, as such, you’ve allowed yourself not to experience so many great things in life.</span></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">The next chain effect of being too comfortable in life is idleness that which causes negative mind-set and attitude. As we’ve observed, idle mind creates negative attitudes and circumstances. There’s even a saying that goes,</span></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"color: rgb(153, 153, 153);\"><em>“An idle mind is the devil’s play ground”</em></strong></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">Because you feel discontented and you have more free time in your hands, you have a great tendency to create negative emotions and thoughts of negativity. This is why people often become more hardened by life because of negative emotion and thoughts. They choose to be in their comfort zone yet they endlessly complain and react instead of being proactive and do something to change their life circumstance.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">Being in our comfort zone leads us to live life without purpose and drive. Because every day, we just do the normal things that we do and expect the same things we normally receive. As such, we don’t see anything special with our day or our life. Have you noticed why successful people are energetic and enthusiastic while unsuccessful people have sour face? Because one is focused and energize to move towards its goal and purpose while the other is unwilling to take risk and just endlessly complain to life hardship or expecting life to be the same.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">Successful people achieve success because they are always in the look-out to grab opportunity at hand. On the other hand, unsuccessful people never achieve success because they wait for things to happen instead of creating it. When you are in your comfort zone, you are part of those who just wait for things to happen. Because unless you take risk and think outside the box, you cannot grab opportunity ahead of others. Being too comfortable causes you to be left behind.</span></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">For a final note, whenever you are faced to choose your comfort zone and be scared to take risk, remember this:</span></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"color: rgb(153, 153, 153);\"><em>We cannot become what we want to be by remaining what we are. We can only change our life, if we are brave enough to be out of our comfort zone. Because the first step to change in your circumstances is a change from within you. –&nbsp;</em></strong><a href=\"http://lifetofullest.com/about-the-author/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\"><strong><em>Lou Macabasco</em></strong></a></p><p><br></p>','97f9fe5010d311e9aade919f5ad6e9db'),(6,'CHAPTER 6',1,6,'c8b63280466411e98b30e9734932299f','c8b63280466411e98b30e9734932299f','2019-01-03 10:27:36','2019-03-14 19:57:49','<p>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Keep your mind clean from dirt –</p><ul><li>Now we are working towards to stabilize our mind through meditation</li><li>We are ready to get out of our comfort zone to achieve abundance</li><li>We have started thinking big out of our limitations</li></ul><p>The next big step is to make consistency of mentioned practices and keep your mind away from all the negativity. One drop of poison makes whole glass of water poisonous. Our complete hard work can go for toss if we are surrounded by toxic negative people or negative circumstances. Let’s learn it and write on big page of paper that we have to be very far from negative influences or practices like:</p><ul><li>Cribbing</li><li>Talking negative for others</li><li>Back biting</li><li>Being in friend circle of negative people</li></ul><p>Its in human nature that negative things influence faster than the positive things. As we have already conveyed that our results or output depends upon the type of input we have. We work very hard to make our mind positive and a one which attracts money. You can imagine what will happen to mind if we feed it with negative inputs. It is rule of nature; output will also become negative. It is that simple, So it is very important to keep our mind free from all negativity.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>','99bbf96010d311e9be6a6d1428e5963a'),(7,'CHAPTER 7',1,7,'1e666570466511e993e147b2beb30b8e','1e666570466511e993e147b2beb30b8e','2019-01-03 10:28:31','2019-03-14 19:58:03','<p>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Value Time –</p><p>You know one very important difference between Rich people and poor &amp; middle class people? Rich treat time more than money. They are occupied and organized. They try to find out value from each second.</p><p>It is not like poor or middle class don’t value time or not organized. But the problem is they are stuck in such a race of money that they are occupied with routine work and hardly get time to see anything outside their routine activities.</p><p>In a simple words value per second of rich is much much higher than value of middle class &amp; poor. Let’s assume if 2000 middle class people are working in a company owned by a rich wealthy guy. That means rich guy has 17,28,00,000 seconds a day to create wealth and a poor or middle class guy working in his company has 86400 seconds a day to create wealth.</p><p>Another category of poor class or middle class is who got all the time of world but don’t know what to do with it. They kill time with unwanted activities. Don’t be surprised if we say more than 70% of worlds population belongs to this category. Problem is not that they don’t have ideas of what to do and what not to do, problem is they never take action. And that is the reason they keep thinking and thinking across their lives.</p><p>We have experimented a lot to learn such people don’t take action and came to conclusion that most of the people are</p><ul><li>Either scared of consequences</li><li>or have habit to procrastinate everything</li></ul><p>Do we need to tell you what is the solution to get rid or both mentioned problem areas?</p><p>Let us explain you in short:</p><p>If you are scared of consequences, please understand what is the risk involved? Risk of loosing home? Risk of loosing job? Risk of loosing relationship? Do you know not taking risk is the biggest risk in life? Anyways you know your situation better and you are the best to answer whether you want to change your life by taking action or want to live with your current situation. But let us conclude this with very short line, “After 1000 failures and just 1 correct action, Electric Bulb was invented by Sir Thomas Edison” So let us fail for 1000 times because we know to become successful, just one correct action is required which can be our 1<sup>st</sup> attempt or 1000<sup>th</sup> attempt.</p><p>If you have a habit of Procrastination? May god help you. This habit is worst that some worst disease which has taken life of more than crores careers. It is not easy to get out of it and we can just request to try for 10 days to do your things right now. Even if it is in some old part of your mind take next 10 days or a month to experiment with yourself to see changes in you when start doing everything – RIGHT NOW. Want to learn Guitar and the plan is pending since years? – Please go and join guitar classes today. Got some business plan since years? – Take action today. Stuck in financial mess since years – take action right today. TIME IS FLYING SO FASTER NOW, DON’T LET YOURSELF LEFT ALONE BECAUSE OF HABIT OF PROCRASTINATION.</p><p>Here we conclude our mindset ARENA. Watch each video again and again till the time it reaches your DNA. Our target is to eat apples for which we have to understand that the first step is to sow seed of apple much inside the ground so that roots go stronger. We cannot expect apples to grow on a tree if we sow mango seeds. So to have financial abundance we have to make our mindset required to attract money. To make roots stronger we have to ensure that we keep practicing everything required to change our mindset required for financial abundance. If mindset is not strong whatever wealth we will earn through lottery or through other means, will not last long.&nbsp;</p>','9bc86b0010d311e9ae0dfdca98467e00'),(8,'CHAPTER 1',2,1,'f373bc1047f011e99314eb17db6e4eb0','f373bc1047f011e99314eb17db6e4eb0','2019-01-03 10:31:52','2019-03-16 19:10:24','<p class=\"ql-align-center\">If given a choice to spend on any of items from the following:</p><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></p><p>90% of time you will spend on items on the left hand side. This has been case since generations and now we are addicted to it. The addiction has gone to the level that we buy vacations on EMI. We buy gadgets on EMI. Recently we have seen sunburn party was available with EMI payment option. This is exciting, isn’t it?</p><p>Actually it should not be exciting. It is just like digging our own grave. This is a worst addiction which will make Travel, gadget, entertainment companies, Banks richer and will leave very big hole on your pockets.</p><p>We have problem with spending habits of people in category B which actually takes most of the money from their pockets to the pockets of people from category A. Our community strongly suggest to always be on a gainer side rather than on a looser side. You decide which side you want to be?</p><ul><li><strong>a money gainer side</strong></li><li><strong>a money loser side.</strong></li></ul><p>We want our community members to become <strong>‘Money Magnet’</strong></p><p>‘Money Magnet’ means wherever you go, whatever you do, whether you sleep or your awake – Money should be attracted to you. Your every action, your every effort will only and only attract money. Sounds not possible, right? It is very much possible.</p><p>There is a big mountain. On one side there are people from category A who are already a money magnet and on another side there are people from category B who always lacks money. This mountain got unique feature. There is water of money which flows from one side to another. The water flows from the side where there is poverty, lack of resources, unhappiness, unfruitfulness and barren to the side which is full of richness of every kind, happiness all over, no scarcity of anything, full of abundance, where there are all the luxurious of the world.</p><p>You decide which side of the mountain you want to be? Scarcity side which is on the right hand side or abundance which is on the left hand side?</p><p>The only rule to live on the left hand side is that you will have to be a ‘Money Magnet’.</p><p>Important question here – how one can become Money Magnet??</p><p>You can become money magnet only and only if you will have ‘Multiple Sources of Income (MSI)</p><p>So if you are like this:</p><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></p><p>Congrats, you are a money magnet and on the left hand side of the mountain</p><p>All the luxuries of the world are waiting for you.</p><p>You can afford anything.</p><p>You are really rich and others give your examples</p><p>Others follow you blindly</p><p>There is happiness across you and 90% populations of the world is working for you.</p><p>Is it that simple to be a money magnet? - No it is not.</p><p>Than how is it possible for a poor or a middle class guy to become a money magnet?</p><p>You want to know how?</p><p>Before sharing, you have to take a pledge that you will change your spending pattern right now -</p><p>If your existing spending pattern is like:</p><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></p><p>Have to change it to:</p><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></p><p>Can you do it?</p><p>If no – we are sorry we don’t know any other way where we can help you to become money magnet</p><p>If yes – you have started your journey to become money magnet</p><p>We will give you all the required logics for changing your spending pattern as mentioned above in later part of video</p>','a37d500010d311e99f29fb9af04f3377'),(9,'CHAPTER 2',2,2,'0c976ca047f111e9be5e91d56ebabfc2','0c976ca047f111e9be5e91d56ebabfc2','2019-01-03 10:32:33','2019-03-16 19:10:48','<p>Money got Multiplication (X) effect?</p><p>Money is the strongest and most powerful instrument available on earth. It got such a huge power that it can rotate entire world around it. Let us tell you the fact that you cannot even have 2 days’ meal without money. People behavior towards you will also depend upon the amount of money you have in your bank or pocket.</p><p>To experiment it see your behavior towards bagger who might be so polite to you and your reaction to him &amp; the very next movement towards your client or friend who gets out of Mercedes. It’s a very fact which you might deny but we know how important money is. So if you still believe money can’t buy everything, it’s a time to wake up.</p><p>Now let us tell you that money works like multiplication (X) effect. You multiply money with anything, will grow further. We will tell you with demonstration:</p><p><strong>Anything X money = more of that anything</strong></p><p>Similarly,</p><p><strong>Assets X money = most assets and money</strong></p><p><strong>Liabilities X money = more liabilities and money</strong></p><p>Let us explain you following formulas in detail.</p><p>Here Assets we mean anything which appreciates in value and liabilities means anything which depreciates in value.</p><ul><li>Money x stocks = more stocks and income</li><li>Money x Mutual Funds = More funds</li><li>Money x Bonds = More money in a form of interest</li><li>Money x Real Estate = More money in form of rent</li><li>Money x Business = More money in form of profits</li><li>Money x Investment = more money in form of returns</li><li>Money x Loans = loss of money</li><li>Money x new car = temporary happiness and comfort + depreciation of money</li><li>Money x Iphone x = temporary happiness + depreciation of money</li><li>Money x Shopping = temporary happiness + depreciation of money</li><li>Money x diamonds = loss of money</li></ul><p>Let us elaborate it little further –</p><ul><li>Money x stocks = more stocks and income</li></ul><p>This will happen only if stocks appreciate in value or give dividend or otherwise it will depreciate in value. So it is very important to understand which asset we invest our money and should study it thoroughly. So if money x stocks = negative income how can we say money got multiplication effect. We will still stick to our point that money has multiplication effect but in above formula the problem was with choosing an asset.</p><p>SO asset can be a BAD ASSET OR A GOOD ASSET.</p><ul><li>Money x good asset = more money</li><li>Money x bad asset = loss of money</li></ul><p>Same is the case with liability – Liability can be a good liability or a bad liability.</p><p>If you take a loan at 9% and invest it in some asset where you get 15%, you will still earn 6 %. In that case, liability actually earned you good amount of money.</p><p><strong>So take away points are:</strong></p><p>Money always acts as a multiplier, the earlier we understand the better will be for your financial life</p><p>It is important to understand and learn asset class before investing in it</p><p>Preference to invest in asset before spending your hard earned money into some liability.</p><p><br></p>','a4d3e92010d311e987308590af13562c'),(10,'CHAPTER 3',2,3,'22399aa047f111e983886979ebb16cf2','22399aa047f111e983886979ebb16cf2','2019-01-03 10:33:17','2019-03-16 19:11:31','<p>Let’s come to our main topic where we want you to change your spending pattern i.e. give first preference to spend on investments and savings and than spend on anything else. We are sure that you are curious to know the reason?</p><p>Are you not?</p><p>The reason we want you to first spend on investments is because we know that money got multiplication effect. So the first preference should always be given to keep on adding assets as money into good assets is always equal to multiplication of money. Thus we can give our chance to increase our good assets and create multiple sources of income. And if you still remember to become money magnet we require MSI’s i.e. money to come from Multiple Sources of Income.</p><p>Our mind is positioned to give last importance to savings and investments. If something remains than only we prefer to save or invest which should be another way round. That is the main reason majority of crowd always remain in either middle class segment or poor class. They keep trying to upscale their financial status but they don’t understand simple dynamics of money and that is the only reason they keep struggling to upscale their financial class.</p><p>We will come in our further chapter where to invest and how to invest but let’s come to the point where we want complete emphasis to give first preference to investment than spend on anything else. We can start with as small amount as possible and can take time frame target of a year. Once we start seeing benefit out of it and bring change in our financial structure, it will change our perception about money all together.</p><p>The first step can be a baby step but important is to take a step. Slowly this habit will enter into our DNA and we will find our self very smart in handling our own money.</p><p>Each asset we have bought since earlier age will start giving us money and that is what we require to become money magnet i.e. to have MSI’s.</p><p>We will start having MSI – Multiple sources of income. Income coming from different assets and filling our bank with abundance. How nice it would be not to have control on incoming money and rather have good control on money going out of our bank. Don’t you want that. Riches already live this life. You can live it too once you have MSI’s.</p><p><strong><em>YOU WILL BECOME A MONEY MAGNET. Whatever you do, wherever you go – MONEY WILL FOLLOW YOU.</em></strong></p>','a67ea96010d311e98bb2ab746a350409'),(11,'CHAPTER 4',2,4,'5ee7a5a047f111e9ae1385e6efa2121d','5ee7a5a047f111e9ae1385e6efa2121d','2019-01-03 10:34:14','2019-03-16 19:12:56','<p>What is Financial Literacy?</p><p>According to <span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Wikipedia – ‘</span><em style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Financial literacy&nbsp;is the ability to understand how money works in the world: how someone manages to earn or make it, how that person manages it, how he/she invests it (turn it into more) and how that person donates it to help others. More specifically, it refers to the set of skills and knowledge that allows an individual to make informed and effective decisions with all of their financial resources</em><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">’</span></p><p><span style=\"color: black;\">According to Investopedia </span><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">– </span><span style=\"color: black;\">‘</span><em>Financial literacy is the education and understanding of various financial areas. This topic focuses on the ability to manage personal finance&nbsp;matters in an efficient manner, and it includes the knowledge of making appropriate decisions about personal finance such as investing, insurance, real estate, paying for college, budgeting, retirement and&nbsp;Tax Planning.</em><span style=\"color: black;\">’</span></p><p>In simple words, financial literacy is the ability to understand how money works in the world. It is about how one manages to earn or make it; how one manages the money made, how he/she invests it, multiplies it and becomes financially independent.</p><p>If we give Rs. 1 Million to two individuals and judge them after 2 years – then their pattern of managing this money will be different. Suppose these two individuals are Rahul &amp; Bheem</p><p>Rahul is a party guy and spends most of time with his friends:</p><ul><li>He bought new branded watch for INR 2 lakhs</li><li>He upgraded his car worth INR 12 Lakhs for which he has taken loan of 6 lakhs. He has given INR 6 lakhs from the amount given to him. His new EMI is INR 8K</li><li>He keeps spending on parties and his remaining amount of INR 2 lakhs washed away in 3 months.</li></ul><p>After 6 months:</p><ul><li>He has to sell his car since he is not able to pay EMI’s</li><li>He lost his friend circle since he is not able to spend on parties anymore</li><li>He sold his watch at half of it’s price as he was in need of money</li><li>He is completely out of pocket</li></ul><p>Now his Rs. 1 Million has almost wiped off as he was not able to handle it. The reason he was not able to handle money is because he was financially not literate.</p><p>Bheem handles this money differently and was active from day one:</p><ul><li>He decides to learn money management on his own and spends 6 months on learning.</li><li>He researched on money making avenues and learnt about property market, stock market, mutual funds, and other avenues which could give good returns.</li><li>He also consulted some of his friends for their advice.</li></ul><p>After a good six-month study and research, he made following investments:</p><ul><li>He invested Rs. 4 lakh in a property with an estimated return of 30%, including the rent.</li><li>He invested Rs. 4 lakh in a fund with an estimated return of 17% p.a</li><li>He invested Rs. 1 lakh in a high risk fund that would either multiply 3 times or depreciate by 50% in a period of 18 months.</li><li>He invested Rs. 1 lakh (20% of the initial capital requirement of Rs. 5 lakh) in fast food startup co-owned by his friend.</li></ul><p>After 2 years:</p><ul><li>His real estate investment gave him 26 % return – a little lesser than the expected 30%, turning his Rs. 400000 into Rs. 504000</li><li>The fund gave him returns of 16% p.a turning Rs. 400000 into Rs. 528000.</li><li>The high risk fund did not perform well depreciated by 50%. So he lost Rs. 50,000 and is left with the remaining Rs. 50,000.</li><li>His investment in the fast food startup gave him very high return, about 88.2%, turning Rs. 1 lakh into Rs. 1,88,200. Since the business is doing very well he decides to remain as a partner in it.</li></ul><p>Now if he decides to spend 50k for his hobbies, parties or any other entertainment – it’s a fair deal. Because he will enjoy from earned money not owned money.</p><p>The above examples are hypothetical and each of them presented a different approach of managing money. Rahul is a typical case which most of the people from group B do in their routine lives. They are attracted to short term pleasures and spend almost entire money on those. What is holidays on EMI, laptop on EMI, Mobile on EMI, everything on EMI – what are those? Short term pleasures which will make your financial life miserable.</p><p>Bheem also likes those short term pleasures. Even he loves to party, want to buy a luxury car and wants to have all the pleasure of life but he is financially literate. He knows that he can achieve all those pleasures and in fact much more if he makes some short term sacrifices and bring on discipline in how he spends.</p><p>He decided to learn how money works, which is the best-suggested way. In the learning process, there are chances that he might lose some money, initially, but in a long run he will learn the nature of money. He will be in a better position to manage his money.</p><p>So, it is important to <strong>educate yourself on financial literacy.</strong></p><p><strong>Further there is need to understand if we should manage our money our self or give it to some expert for handling?</strong></p><p>The point is <strong>whether you should give the steering of your finances in someone else’s hands or take steering on your own hands</strong>. That call is up to you but you need to understand that you should know driving even if you want to give your steering in someone else’s hands as it is not safe to blindly trust an advisor whose skills and merit is unknown to you.</p><p>You can give your steering of finances in someone else’s hands but only if you know driving yourself, you will be able to reach your destination. And if you your self is a good driver, try to keep the steering in your own hands.</p>','a852af2010d311e9a38db32bb6f34a36'),(12,'CHAPTER 5',2,5,'728b24f047f111e9b0b759630ca0950c','728b24f047f111e9b0b759630ca0950c','2019-01-03 10:35:45','2019-03-16 19:13:36','<p><strong>Let’s try to understand how money works:</strong></p><p>Money rotates every single minute where somebody will earn it and somebody will lose it. Every transaction you do, there will be winners and losers. When you visit a restaurant and pay the bill, hotel owner is the winner of your money and you are the loser of your money. When you buy Pepsi, you are making owners of Pepsi rich. This is how money works and you have to decide whether you want to be on the gainer\'s side or loser\'s side? This simple examples should give you an idea about how money rotates.</p><p>Let us try to understand this with an example which will give you good idea on how money works:</p><p>If you take a loan of Rs. 1000000 for 5 years at 14% interest, the calculations will look like:</p><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></p><p>Therefore, you will pay total Rs. 1396095 in next 5 years</p><p>Now let us examine this in reverse way and see if we invest same EMI of Rs. 23268 in some investment opportunity, which gives us same returns @ 14% per annum. Let us see what happens?</p><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></p><p>So it is to be noted that 5 years ago if we took a loan, we get to use only Rs. 1000000 and will have to pay INR 1396080 in return and if we invest the same amount (EMI) then the money grows to more than double of the loan principal to an amount of Rs. 2028987.</p><p>This seems like a magic, isn’t it? This magic is called <strong><em>Power of Compounding</em></strong>. Banks have created their empires with this magical word <strong><em>Power of Compounding</em></strong>. In simple words, money will create more money.</p><p><strong style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Now you would understand why we want you to change your spending habits. We want you to start investing as small as you can and as early as possible.</strong></p><p>Start with investing a small amount, early in life; you will be surprised to see your wealth with time.&nbsp;If I ask you to invest Rs. 5000 every month when you are 21 and keep investing for next 20 years till the time you are 40 and suppose your money grows at 15% per annum. Then you will get a huge amount of Rs. 6581731. So actually you have invested Rs.12 lakh overall in 20 years and you will get in return Rs. 6581731 after 20 years, which is more than five times of the amount invested.</p><p>We have still not come to where to invest and how to invest. We are still stuck to the point that there is need to change spending habits and we will try even harder to emphasize on this point so that you should understand that we should start growing assets and reduce liabilities if we really want to get rich in our life.</p><p>Hope you got the meaning of financial literacy without which it is not possible to grow financially beyond certain point.&nbsp;</p>','aa84193010d311e9ad95ed56d7cc38ac');
INSERT INTO `chapters` VALUES (13,'CHAPTER 6',2,6,'8a11b6d047f111e9abd765dc558fba99','8a11b6d047f111e9abd765dc558fba99','2019-01-03 10:39:58','2019-03-16 19:14:13','<p><strong>How dangerous is financial illiteracy?</strong></p><p>Financially illiteracy is the most dangerous thing in life. We have heard lot of stories where people do quite well in life because of professional career but start struggling once they are out of their profession. Cricketers and movie stars are best example of financial illiteracy. They enjoy best luxuries of life till the time they are professionally active. Once they are out of their profession they start struggling financially. Because they are not financially literate. That is the reason we say financial illiteracy is the most dangerous thing in life.</p><p>This is not only the case with only such professionals but with most of people in business or salaried people. They work very hard through out their lives but never find themselves achieve financial greatness. The only reason is because they are not financial literate.</p><p>Eg of financial illiteracy:</p><p><strong>Example 1:</strong></p><ul><li>Abhishek works with a big multinational company.</li><li>His take home salary is Rs. 80,000 per month.</li><li>He got married and recently bought a 2bhk flat.</li><li>Cost of the flat is Rs. 80L. He arranged Rs. 40L from his savings and took a home loan of Rs. 40L from a bank.</li><li>The EMI of his home loan is Rs. 40k per month and his regular household expenses is Rs. 20k per month.</li><li>He bought a car worth Rs. 10L of which he paid Rs. 3 lakh from his savings and took a car loan of Rs. 7 lakh.</li><li>The EMI for the car loan is Rs. 14k.</li><li>So his saving is Rs. 6000.</li><li>His only source of income is his salary.</li><li>The thought of losing his job makes him sick.</li><li>He is stuck in a financial mess.</li><li>Some sudden expenses will destroy his stability.&nbsp;</li></ul><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></p><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></p><p>Don’t you think most of the salaried people are part of situation like this?</p><p><strong>Example 2:</strong></p><ul><li>Vishal is having his own retail business of an Ice-cream Parlor.</li><li>To start this business, he has taken a loan of Rs. 15 lakh from his relative.</li><li>He earns around Rs. 1 lakh per month. His earning decreases during the rainy and winter season and rises in the summer season.</li><li>His average earning is Rs.1 lakh per month.</li><li>He pays Rs.30k as an interest for the loan he has taken.</li><li>His monthly household expenses are Rs. 40k.</li><li>He is addicted to buying new gadgets, perfumes, clothes and other accessories and spends nearly Rs. 30k per month to meet these expenses.</li><li>Thus he hardly saves his earning.&nbsp;</li></ul><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></p><p>Just imagine what will be his situation if a competitor comes in the same area and affects his ice-cream parlour sales? There by reducing his income.</p><p>This might severely impact his lifestyle, as he is not ready with an alternative source of income and neither has any savings.</p><p><strong>Where is the problem?</strong></p><p>Is Abhishek salary not good enough? Or, is Vishal not earning adequately to meet his needs?</p><p>No, the <strong>problem is something else</strong>.</p><p>You can have handsome salary because of your domain knowledge or skills.</p><p>You can have wonderful business expertise and can earn good profits in your business.</p><ul><li>But still it is possible that you may not take proper care of your earned money and keep struggling for it all your life.</li><li>The problem is that both are financially illiterate.</li></ul><p>We have seen a majority of people struggling financially because of less avenues of income or lack of knowledge of income generation avenues and due to poor financial planning and management.</p><p>Then how is it possible that:</p><ul><li>Few people get richer and richer.</li><li>They get revenues from almost wherever they invest</li><li>They have many sources of income</li><li>They own a lot of properties</li><li>They have a huge bank balance</li><li>They lend money to others</li></ul><p>While many others at the same time:</p><ul><li>Struggle financially throughout life</li><li>They work very hard for living</li><li>Borrow money and keep working to repay it</li><li>They are scared of failures</li><li>They try different businesses but never succeed in any</li><li>They believe money can only be earned through hard work</li><li>They are scared of taking risks</li><li>They struggle to meet their basic necessities</li><li>They keep planning but never gather enough courage to implement their plans</li><li>They feel unlucky</li></ul><p>Have you ever imagined why it is so?</p><p>We heard the phrase - Money earns Money!</p><p>Than how come the Founder of Facebook, who was a middle class man, is now one of the richest people on the earth? He became lucky?</p><p>You may have heard of many people where a poor or a middle class man climbed the ladder of success and has become rich now. How is it so?&nbsp;Did they all become lucky? Is it possible?</p><p>But have you not heard the stories of children of wealthy people who were unable to handle the legacy and are struggling financially? Then how is their money is not earning money for them?</p><p>We can say, money is important to earn more money but without having <strong><em><u>financial literacy</u></em></strong>, it is impossible to multiply your money. It is impossible to grow your money.</p><p>The main problem with 90% of people who dream big is that they lose focus mid-way due to their financial problems. This starts with small bad financial habits that lead us into a major financial blunder.</p><p>Eg:</p><p>Here is an example on how we common people have our spending habits.</p><p>Vikram is 22 years old and has started a catering businessfrom which he earns around Rs. 20000 – 30000 per month. He is a bachelor and spends a lot of time partying with his friends. His personal expenses are Rs. 15000. He gives Rs. 10000 to his family and pays Rs. 5000 towards his credit card bill. He does not invest as he’s left with no money.</p><p>Six years later, he got married. He has also expanded is clientele and now earns Rs. 80k a month. He still parties a lot but now with his family and spends Rs. 25000 a month on it. He has a surplus expenditure Rs. 10000 a month. He bought a car and pays EMI of Rs. 15000 per month. He gives Rs. 20000 a month at his home. His credit card bill cost him Rs. 10000 per month. Even after his income grew he does not invest as he is left with no money at the end of the month.</p><p>Vikram is 33 years old now and has a daughter. His business is doing well and he earns Rs. 1 lakh per month. He bought new house with a loan of Rs. 40L. He also upgraded his car with the help of a car loan. He pays EMI of Rs. 40000 towards home loan and Rs. 25000 towards car loan. He has household expenses of Rs. 25000 a month. He spends Rs. 5000 on partying. His credit card bill stands Rs. 10000 per month. He still doesn’t save or invest money as he spends everything he earns.</p><p>Now, after 35 years, his business is saturated. His expenses are increasing and income is uneven. Household expenses have soared and he cannot afford parties anymore. To meet the increased expenses, he took a loan of Rs. 3lakh from a bank whose EMI is Rs. 8000 per month. His monthly income is Rs. 70000 and monthly expenses are Rs. 1 lakh.&nbsp;</p><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></p><p>He is in <strong>financial mess</strong> since his expenses are more than his income. He has to sell his car, degrade the quality of his daughter’s education to manage the increasing expenses. This is a common example of financial illiteracy. Majority of the people in our society face such a situation due to lack of financial planning.</p><p><strong>We get stuck into a ‘Financial Mess’ when your monthly expenses exceed your monthly income. </strong></p><p>Investment or saving is a life skill that is never taught in any school or college. Henceforth many literate people are financially illiterate. They lack the knowledge of investment avenues and have little or no financial planning. This happens because we are accustomed to plan the spending rather than saving. When we start earning, we fall for the love of spending money, as our income increases our expenses also increase and we hardly save anything. Easy availability of credit cards and EMI schemes further complicates this problem as we spend more than our income. Thus leading ourselves into a financial mess.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>How do the banks and other financial institutions make profit?</p><ul><li>Banks give us lower interest rate on our savings and lend money at higher interest rates.</li><li>Banks give credit cards to encash on our spending habits. We have around 45 days to repay the credit card bill without any penalty. However, if we fail to do so, they charge us penalty along with the interest on outstanding bill.</li></ul><p>Banks are very well aware of bad spending habits of common people and leverage the opportunity. They design products keeping in mind financial illiteracy of majority of people and get rich.</p><p><strong>Spending habits of financial illiterate people:</strong></p><p><strong>Model of Financially Mess People:</strong></p><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></p><ol><li>They always prefer to complete their luxuries first and hardly give any importance to buying any asset</li><li>They keep on spending on liabilities till the time liabilities suck up their entire financial system.</li><li>They finally enter into a ‘Financial Mess Circle’ where they have to compulsorily earn just to take care of their liabilities</li><li>They do not understand the concept of passive income and just keep increasing their liabilities. They don’t plan for future.</li><li>They have a variety of credit cards</li></ol><p><br></p>','aca857e010d311e9bfbb3d191501e294'),(14,'CHAPTER 7',2,7,'c201825047f111e9a99c29113cdb082a','c201825047f111e9a99c29113cdb082a','2019-01-03 10:41:35','2019-03-16 19:16:36','<p><strong>Ultimate objective - Financial Independence</strong></p><p><strong>When in our life can we say that we are financially successful?</strong></p><p>Why do we earn &amp; save money? Why do we want to multiply it? Why we require money in our life? Or what is a need to become financial literate?</p><p>We save money, wants to multiply it or require it in life to fulfill financial goals like:</p><ul><li>buying our own house</li><li>buying a vehicle</li><li>children’s educational expenses</li><li>children’s marriage</li><li>post-retirement fund and so on</li></ul><p>Our want for money never ends but some of the above reasons are valid enough and fulfilling them gives us a sense of fulfillment and achievement. But let us tell you our financial goals will keep increasing or are unending. Financial goals keep changing with time, for example:When you plan for your children’s educational expenses and start investing money to build corpus for it, other short-term goals may take priority,such as building fund for a family vacation and so on.</p><p>Financial planners are good at designing and convincing you to create your financial goals and start creating corpus for it. However, we believe a better approach is,<strong> “Instead of targeting your financial goals, let’s target financial independence”</strong></p><p><strong>You can say that you are financially successful when you become financially independent</strong></p><p><strong>Financial independence is the stage in your life when your passive income takes care of your basic/routine expenses, your luxuries, and your financial goals.</strong></p><ul><li>Example:</li></ul><p>Rajesh’s,</p><p>Monthly expenses = Rs. 30000</p><p>Vacation every month = Rs. 15000</p><p>Loan for Car = Rs. 15000</p><p>_______________________________________</p><p>Total Expenses = Rs. 60000</p><p>Rajesh’s monthly Salary is Rs. 100000</p><p>Therefore, he can easily pay his monthly expenses from his salary but he is not financiallyindependent as since he has to pay all these expenses from his basic monthly income, which is his active income. So if his active income stops or depletes then his financial situation will deteriorate, pulling him into a financial mess.</p><p>In above case how Rajesh can become financially independent?</p><p>Suppose, he had invested in a property, 10 years ago, which is now giving him a high, monthly return as a rent of Rs. 70000. All his monthly expenses are met fromthis rent. Even if he spends most of the rent, he is left with Rs. 10000 per month. Now, he can be called as a Financial Independent person since he doesn’t have to work for his expenses.</p><p><strong>The ULTIMATE OJECTIVE should always be to become financially independent. You can call yourself financially successful once you are able to achieve this feat.</strong></p><p><strong>Spending pattern of Financially Independent people</strong></p><p><strong>[IMAGE]</strong></p><p>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;They prefer to buy some asset from their regular income before spending even a penny on increasing any liability. They believe that increase in asset will further boost up their monthly income.</p><p>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Asset starts giving them passive income and in turn, they invest the same again to buy more assets. They spend part of income from passive income to enjoy their luxury dreams.</p><p>3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;They keep on increasing assets until the time their total monthly expenses are easily met by their passive income.</p><p>4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;At one stage, they don’t have to think about their financial dreams since they earn handsome passive income to fulfill them.</p><p>5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;They believe in struggle until the time they create good assets to create passive income. They don’t prefer to spend on liabilities from their active income</p><p>6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;They don’t use credit cards</p><p><br></p>','aea678c010d311e9ba6edf4589c7dd16'),(15,'CHAPTER 8',2,8,'06d0559047f211e9bed8516444dc9ea5','06d0559047f211e9bed8516444dc9ea5','2019-01-03 10:44:56','2019-03-16 19:18:26','<p>Imagine if you are sent to a battlefield with a machine gun, without teaching you how to operate it! You will be killed in seconds. Similarly, before moving to the most important topics on how to earn passive income and how to create wealth, let us first learn some financial statements without which it will not be possible to monitor your progress.</p><p>To analyze your financial status you will need to understand the following terms:</p><p><strong>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Cash Flow Statement</strong></p><p><strong>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Balance Sheet</strong></p><p>[IMAGE]</p><p><strong>Cash flow Statement</strong></p><p>It will give you a clear understanding of the cash inflow and help you analyse your expenses. It presents a systematic picture of all your income sources and your spending pattern, giving you a clear picture of your financial status. The Net Monthly Cash Flow should always be positive.</p><p>On the left hand side i.e. income side, list your income from all the sources. First let us understand the income section in detail:</p><p>[IMAGE]</p><ul><li><strong>Active Income</strong> – Income, which is earned through our direct effort, is known as active income. We work daily to earn it. Income from salary, wages, and business where we are involved for full time, part time, professional income comes under this category.</li><li><strong>Passive income</strong> – We have discussed it in detail in further part of this video. To give a brief - <span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">An income for which you do not work directly such as the income from rent, business in which you aren’t directly involved, interest from various investments, dividends, royalties, and so on form passive income. Once we start accumulating ‘assets’, passive income begins to increase.</span></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">When your passive income is more than your expenses, per month, then you are financially independent.</span></p><p>[IMAGE]</p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">On the right hand side of cash flow statement, list all your expenses. A substantial portion of our income is used to pay various taxes. Other expenses such as utility bills, maintenance, credit card bill, loan EMI, and so on must be listed here.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">We must focus on keeping our expenses under control. When we start accumulating liabilities, expenses tend to increase. </span></p><p><strong style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Total Income – Total Expenses = Net Monthly Cash Flow</strong></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">If,</span><strong style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"> Passive income – Total Expenses = Positive Net Monthly Cash Flow</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">, then you are financially independent.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">If, </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Total Income – Total Expenses = Negative Net Monthly Cash Flow</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">, then you are in financial mess.</span></p><p><strong>Asset - </strong>In accounting terms, asset means any instrument/ valuable possession we invest money into that we own/ benefit from, that generate income.</p><p>Let’s try to break it up in simple words.</p><p>When we spend money to buy some investment instruments such as, stocks, which gives us dividends (profit), then we have invested in an asset. If we spend money to buy some property, which gives us, good rental incomes then we have invested in an asset.</p><p>[IMAGE]</p><p>Now asset can either:</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Create wealth or</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Give regular passive income </strong></p><ul><li>If you buy a Mutual Fund which is not giving us monthly returns but growing rapidly in value, it means that the asset is creating wealth.</li><li>If you have invested in a shop that is not increasing in value but gives you regular monthly rent, it means the asset is giving regular passive income</li></ul><p>Further asset can be a good asset or bad asset. In above examples where asset has or gives us some returns, can be termed as a good asset. If our asset is not giving us any returns, and the money seems to be blocked, it can be termed as a dead asset or bad asset. For example, a property where there is no appreciation and not giving us any rental income, we can say that we have blocked our money in bad asset.</p><p>In accounting terms, if we spend our money on certain items like:</p><ul><li>Purchasing computers for business</li><li>Cash in hand</li><li>Inventory</li><li>Buying vehicle</li></ul><p>and so on are considered to be asset even if they don’t give us direct returns. These assets are termed as ‘Non-Productive Assets’.</p><p>As a term in financial literacy, we will consider only those things as asset, which can give us some returns against our investment in them. Let us term those assets as productive assets. It is difficult to understand whether an asset will be a bad asset or a good asset, for now, let us assume all the assets will be productive assets.</p><p>Money spent to buy home for ourselves, from whom we are not earning any income can be termed as ‘Non-<strong>Productive Asset’.</strong></p><ul><li>Increase in productive-assets will lead to an increase in passive income and wealth. Therefore, our financial objective should be to create productive-assets</li><li>Note that productive-asset can be immaterial things like Business Empire, goodwill, brand which can be created over a period of time. All these things also have monetary value.</li></ul><p><strong>Liability</strong> - In accounting terms liability refers to the state of being responsible for something, and this term can refer to any money or service owed to another party. For example, if we borrow some money from a friend to expand our business than we can refer to it a liability, as we are liable to pay that amount to our friend.&nbsp;</p><p>[IMAGE]</p><p>Loan taken to buy home which is not giving us any returns as rental income is a liability.</p><p>Liability is bad only if we spend it on buying a bad asset or on luxury items.</p><ul><li>Just imagine taking a loan from bank at @14% and spending it on holidays.</li><li>Borrowing money from friend @ 20% and spending it on purchasing a mobile phone</li><li>Using your credit card to buy clothes and paying later in installment. If you take liability for spending habits like this, then it is bad.</li></ul><p>Liability is good, if we spend it usefully.</p><ul><li>Example: Taking home loan for a property @9.5% which is giving you yearly rental of almost 11-12%&nbsp;&nbsp;(Including rate appreciation)</li><li>Taking vehicle loan @10% and using that vehicle as commercial one and earning 20-25% on the loan taken.</li><li>Taking business loan @14% pa and earning 20-25% profit from that business.</li></ul><p><strong>Total Assets – Total Liability = Net worth (Our Value)</strong></p><ul><li><strong>If Productive Assets &gt; Total Liability-Sound Position</strong></li><li><strong>If Total Liability &gt; Total Assets-Financial Mess</strong></li></ul><p>These statements should be prepared as frequently as possible to understand our financial position. It should be prepared every week or at least every month to understand where we are heading towards. You can find a template of both these statements on our website.</p><p><br></p>','b07fe01010d311e9969459f6da0f1ccc'),(16,'CHAPTER 1',3,1,'4ad815a047f211e9a6538165c916ae04','4ad815a047f211e9a6538165c916ae04','2019-01-03 10:46:02','2019-03-16 19:21:39','<p><strong>We didn’t mean not to spend on luxuries and entertainment at all?</strong></p><p>By whatever we have taught till now it is felt that we are trying to say not to spend on luxuries and entertainment at all. That is completely wrong. In fact, we would want everyone to have all the luxurious available on earth.</p><ul><li>Big House,</li><li>Luxurious Car,</li><li>Private Yacht</li><li>Private Jet</li><li>Most expensive watches</li></ul><p>Every damn thing</p><p>But we just emphasize that only passive income should be spent on luxuries and entertainment. If we spend active income to buy necessities and luxuries, we will find our self in financial mess which we have discussed in our earlier topic. By now you all should be aware of the meaning of Passive Income.</p><p>Just to revise back, there are two types of income</p><ul><li><strong>Active Income</strong></li><li><strong>Passive Income</strong></li></ul><p><strong style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Active income</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">&nbsp;refers to&nbsp;</span><strong style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">income</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">&nbsp;received from performing a service. This includes wages, tips, salaries, commissions and&nbsp;</span><strong style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">income</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">&nbsp;from businesses in which there is material participation. For example, an accountant who works for a monthly paycheck receives&nbsp;</span><strong style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">active income</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: black;\">Imagine if you could earn money simply by sitting back and doing nothing. Believe it or not, it\'s something countless folks do every day. It\'s a concept known as </span><strong style=\"color: black;\">passive income</strong><span style=\"color: black;\">, and it\'s what allows people like you to accumulate wealth without having to lift a finger.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: black;\">Passive income essentially works like this: You make an initial investment, which generally requires you to not only put up some money, but do some legwork or research. But from that point on, you sit back and enjoy an income stream without having to make any more of a substantial effort. Some common investments known to generate passive income are stocks, bonds, rental properties, or investments in private businesses. All of these ideas allow you to keep generating cash flow over time.&nbsp;</span></p>','d36376c010d311e994a4bb2077939560'),(17,'CHAPTER 2',3,2,'bc529a8047f311e9a09c5b484c7e2115','bc529a8047f311e9a09c5b484c7e2115','2019-01-03 10:46:54','2019-03-16 19:29:59','<p><strong>Where are Opportunities?</strong></p><p>Just look around you. What a world it is full of opportunities. We have massive population which keeps spending day in day out. What else we require? Opportunities all over. Just look around yourself – big houses, fancy cars, big malls with beautiful brands. What a life we can have? With internet so commonly used, size of the world has shrunk further. Just opportunities and opportunities.</p><p>You cannot see opportunities, right?</p><p>Friends, please understand you will understand only those things which you understand. How will you understand things which you have not ever heard of? If you are an accountant and we discuss some opportunity of carbon trading – how will you understand? So the problem is with people discussing carbon trading in front of you or yourself who only understand things related to accounts?</p><p>Please think hard my friend. We don’t see opportunities only and only because we have limited scope of understanding. We are not yet exposed to the world to see opportunity in every thing. Money is being earned every second, every movement – open your eyes and see around you. So many shops, so many malls, so many cabs, so many IT parks, lovely restaurants, big hotels – obviously money is being circulated everywhere.</p><p>So anyone around you if says that there are no opportunities left – please give hard slap and explain the problem is with him the one who cannot see opportunities. Every movement every second opportunities are flying all over, it is just we have to identify the right one and materialize it.</p><p>Just understand, the more exposure you have the more you will be able to judge any opportunity. Riches of the world travel across the world, they are keen to learn new things and that is the reason they can find opportunities out of nothing. There are 2 magic mantras which will help you to learn and understand new things and thus find out opportunities.</p><p><strong>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Read more books</strong></p><p><strong>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Meet lot of people</strong></p><p>Your knowledge is restricted to your boundaries and by reading books you just cross your boundaries of understanding. You will learn things which you might not have heard of. If you try to find out habits of successful people, one thing you will get in common. They read a lot. Because they know that reading will expand their knowledge. And today is a world of knowledge. Today being digital world, knowledge holds lot of power.</p><p>Successful people meet lot and lot of people. We will cover it in detail in our next topic i.e. networking.</p><p>So now onwards please never ever think that there are no opportunities left. We should know and learn to create out of nothing.</p>','d463e4b010d311e984f16313cd65eeb9'),(18,'CHAPTER 3',3,3,'cdf96b5047f311e9a0ff150a1786095d','cdf96b5047f311e9a0ff150a1786095d','2019-01-03 10:47:51','2019-03-16 19:30:33','<p><strong>Value Per Second</strong></p><p>There are 86400 seconds in a day.</p><p>You might not believe if we tell you that there are people who make money in every available second in a day. There are people who earn more than more than 1 $ per second. And believe us they are not from any other planet. You will be puzzled how they earn it?</p><p>It is impossible to work for every available second in a day but it is very much possible to make other people work for you for every available moment. In those terms it is also possible to make your money work for you for every available moment in a day. Such type of income is possible only through passive income where you don’t have to work for money. Other people or money will work for you so that you can earn all available 86400 seconds in a day.</p><p>Let’s see present - Try to calculate how much you earn every second?</p><p>You will not be happy to learn that most of your seconds in life go unutilized or without making any money.</p><p>How good it would be if each available second makes some money for us? If you would have multiple sources of passive income, it is very much possible. We know individuals who actually calculate their value per second. If they give particular time to anyone they value it per second.</p><p>How nice it would be if our time seconds are also valued in money?</p><p>Let’s work towards direction where we can say that don’t waste my time – my each second is valued at $1. So from today onwards work towards direction to increase your value per second. That will be possible if we will have multiple sources of passive income. Ideally an individual should have 6-7 sources of passive income to become financially independent.</p>','d60159e010d311e9ae724d6630dfbbac'),(19,'CHAPTER 4',3,4,'04a140e047f411e9a09e254d395a327b','04a140e047f411e9a09e254d395a327b','2019-01-03 10:50:41','2019-03-16 19:31:56','<p>While going for any opportunity understanding your risk appetite is very important. You need to identity what is your category and accordingly you can go for passive income opportunity. Please note in any type of investment if you expect high returns risk will be higher as well and if you don’t want to take higher risk return will be lower.</p><p>So, you need to identify you belong to which category:</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>High Risk High Returns</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Medium Risk Medium Returns</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Low Risk Low Returns</strong></p><p>Now let’s speak something practical on how passive income can be generated. In this 21<sup>st</sup> century, size of world is shrinking which creates lot of opportunities. There are changes every day, every hour, every minute, every second. Believe us or not your income is indirectly depending upon the pace you are able to predict changes in the world. For eg – Warren Buffet invested in insurance segment in India with a logic that India is a vast country with more than 80% of population is not yet insured. It is just one of the logic and a prediction which might pay off over a period of time. If it pays off, he will earn huge on his investments. For passive income such instincts and study is very important.</p><p>Secondly, as world is getting smaller you have to learn to unlearn things. There were methods which worked out quite well at one point of time which might not work in a given period. For passive income you might encounter with lot of situations where your strategies or methods may not work at all. And there are people who will keep trying. So if you really want to earn passive income -&nbsp;you will have to learn to unlearn things. Or you will find yourself completely outdated. Yahoo.com was such a hit and now hardly anyone uses it. If you are not comfortable with new avenues like Facebook or LinkedIn – you will find yourself outdated.</p><p>How Passive Income could be earned:</p><p>Passive income could be earned through:</p><ul><li><strong>&nbsp;Ideas</strong></li><li><strong>&nbsp;Money</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Passive Income through Ideas:</strong></p><p><strong>Dhirubhai Ambani <em>- ‘Idea’s are no one’s monopoly’</em></strong></p><p>Very rightly said.</p><p>Who knew that a man can fly one day before Airplane was invented by Wright Brothers?</p><p>Who knew that man can communicate from one place to another through a device called telephone before it was invented by Graham Bell.</p><p>All these things were out of anyone’s imagination before it came in mind of someone in a form of idea which actually got executed for mankind. And inventors not only got rich but also got their name written in history books.</p><p>And the good part is that there is no money required to generate an idea. Just you need to think out of the box and before everyone else. And with digitalization it has become very easy to showcase your idea and make money.</p><p>We come up with 1000’s of ideas but unless we execute it, we will never taste success. And the good part is we require to succeed only once before failing 99 times and we will be called successful.</p><p>We are giving few examples on how people used ideas to generate passive income so that you can relate to it and can think of creating something of your own:</p><ul><li>Eg 1 - Youtubing is one of the way where you can create videos of your interest and post it on youtube. The more views you have the more money you make. There are lot of youtubers who create videos and post on youtube. Infact it is full time profession for money people now a day.</li><li>Eg 2 – Writing Ebook and posting on amazon is one of the way where people write about their hobbies, interests, experience or create some story – create a book and post it on amazon.com. They make millions without investing anything</li><li>Eg 3 – Writing blogs is quite popular where you can generate good amount of traffic and earn good amount of income</li><li>Eg 4 – If you are good photographer – Click Good pics and post it on free money making websites like classhot.com where you will be paid by posting pics you click from mobile. If it gets sold you can earn handsomely.</li><li>Eg 5 – Create some informative website of your hobby and sell space on website</li><li>Eg 6 – Make youtube tutorials which can attract crowd and you make passive income</li><li>Eg 7 – You can rent your car and earn passive income</li></ul><p>Actually there are endless things people are doing through ideas and generating good amount of passive income. And the point is idea requires execution to generate actual income.</p><p>If others can earn excellent passive income through ideas, why can’t you – it just requires right idea at right time.</p><p>Start thinking before your idea flies away</p><p><strong>Make your expertise a source for you to earn passive income</strong></p><p>Moreover, every one got one or the other skill. Somebody is good in dancing, somebody in singing, somebody in cooking and so on. You need to find find out your CORE COMPETENCY and UTILIZE IT FOR MANKIND. Believe us it has done wonders for us and will do it for you as well.</p><p>Eg – you are good in cycling. How can you materialize it for passive income:</p><ul><li><strong>You can start right from basic. Like creating a website which gives details of types of cycles available in the market with pricing. Make ecommerce portal to sell and make affiliation with all the cycle companies</strong></li><li><strong>Arrange cycling race, try to get sponsor ship and promote it big time</strong></li><li><strong>You can start writing a blog on every part of cycle, how it is manufactured and how it is finally assembled</strong></li><li><strong>Create health club for cyclers around the world. Create channel so that each one can link to all other cyclers around the world.</strong></li><li><strong>You can start e-tutorials on professional cycling</strong></li><li><strong>There are tones of different ideas you can do with your profession or your liking.</strong></li></ul><p>Most importantly if you make your hobby or liking as a profession – chances to get succeed will be tremendous as passion will come as a complimentary in a business.</p><p>Same way we can think out of the box and can apply same innovative ways of earning out of our hobbies. What else we require for passive income?</p><p><br></p>','d7a103b010d311e99ee27322496b4380'),(20,'CHAPTER 5',3,5,'281e602047f411e987f3f1acc627f310','281e602047f411e987f3f1acc627f310','2019-01-03 10:52:06','2019-03-16 19:33:00','<p><strong>Passive Income through Money:</strong></p><p>Money invested in</p><ul><li><strong>Shares</strong></li><li><strong>Mutual Funds</strong></li><li><strong>Debentures</strong></li><li><strong>Real Estate</strong></li><li><strong>PMS</strong></li><li><strong>Business</strong></li><li><strong>Sleeping Partner</strong></li></ul><p>Can give very good passive income returns. Investment in these sources can range from INR 100 to unlimited. We will discuss each opportunity one by one.</p><ul><li><strong>Shares</strong>:</li></ul><p>Buying shares of any company means you are buying ownership in that company to the extent of quantity of shares bought. Eg – If a retail outlet chain is expanding rapidly with increase in volumes and profits. You are very optimistic about future of that company and would like to become owner of that company. It is possible if that company is listed with Stock Exchange and you buy shares of that company through stock exchange. There are 2 stock exchanges which contributes to maximum turnover in India</p><ul><li><strong>National Stock Exchange</strong></li><li><strong>Bombay Stock Exchange</strong></li></ul><p>Stock Exchanges are just like shopping Malls where you can go to buy and purchase shares of any company. Earlier people use to go to exchanges to buy and sell shares now everything happens online. In fact, even shares you buy are kept in digital format in your DEMAT account. DEMAT account is just like bank account. The way you can keep your money in bank account, shares are kept in your DEMAT account.</p><p>Company requires money to grow. Whenever company feels that they can give share of its company to normal public and thus raise money from general public they issue those shares in the form of Initial Public Offering(IPO). IPO is the way through which company sells its shares to normal public before it is listed on stock exchanges for trading. Normal value of share is INR 10 which is also called face value of share at which company raises money. Company feel that since they are already doing good business they should take some premium from normal public that is why share at which company brings IPO is always higher than face value of share. Company decides price band at which they would want people to buy its shares. People apply to buy shares and on the basis of demand, shares are given to investors which are directly transferred to DEMAT account.</p><p>Shares are than listed on stock exchange where people who bought shares are free to sell on stock exchanges. Also someone who missed out to buy shares through IPO can buy it through exchanges. This Market is known as Secondary Market and buying of shares through IPO is called buying in Primary Market. Usually if demand of share is good – shares trades at higher value than the price given through IPO and vice versa. This is how anyone can invest in stock market or share market.</p><p>There are lot of advantages of investing in stocks:</p><ul><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Investment Gains</strong></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: black;\">One of the primary benefits of investing in the stock market is the chance to grow your money. Over time, the stock market tends to rise in value, though the prices of individual stocks rise and fall daily. Investments in stable companies that are able to grow tend to make profits for investors. Likewise, investing in many different stocks will help build your wealth by leveraging growth in different sectors of the economy, resulting in a profit even if some of your individual stocks lose value.</span></p><ul><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Dividend Income</strong></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: black;\">Some stocks provide income in the form of a dividend. While not all stocks offer dividends, those that do deliver annual payments to investors. These payments arrive even if the stock has lost value and represent income on top of any profits that come from eventually selling the stock. Dividend income can help fund a retirement or pay for even more investing as you grow your investment portfolio over time.</span></p><ul><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Diversification</strong></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: black;\">For investors who put money into different types of investment products, a stock market investment has the benefit of providing diversification. Stock market investments change value independently of other types of investments, such as bonds and real estate. Holding stock can help you weather losses to other investment products. Stock also adds risk to a portfolio, as well as the potential for large, rapid gains, helping investors avoid risk-averse or overly conservative investment strategies.</span></p><ul><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Ownership</strong></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: black;\">Buying shares of stock means taking on an ownership stake in the company you purchase stock in. This means that investing in the stock market also brings benefits that are part of being one of a business\'s owners. Shareholders vote on corporate board members and certain business decisions. They also receive annual reports to learn more about the company. Owning stock in the company you work for can be a way to express loyalty and tie your personal finances to the success of the business as a whole.</span></p><p>Way to invest in Stock Market:</p><ul><li>Step 1 - Before buying any share and investor should define clear objective like why he is investing in stock market. Like he is buying it for passive income, or he is buying to for long term gains or appreciation.</li><li>Step 2 – Investor than should find out which sector will boom for next 1 year, 3 years, 5 years and 10 years</li><li>Step 3 – Investor than should find out good shares available in selected sectors and try to find out intrinsic value of those shares. Intrinsic value is an ideal value at which share should trade in market as per its current book value and Market.</li><li>Step 4 – After finding value, that company should be compared with other good companies in that sector.</li><li>Step 5 – Investor should find out EPS of the company – EPS means how much each share is earning and compare it with competition.</li><li>Step 6 – Investor should find out PE ratio – PE ratio means price earning ratio which means how many times the share is trading in market as compare to its earnings.</li><li><strong>Formula of PE ratio is EPS/Market Price Per share</strong></li></ul><p>Ideally if you are value investor you should select stocks which trades at PE of 15 or less</p><ul><li>Step 7 – Once shares are selected you can also look after few important ratios like current ratio, liquid ratio, dividend history etc</li><li>Step 8 – Once you are convinced with business plan of the selected company and the price it is trading at make sense to enter. You should look out how many shares you want to buy over a period of time. Than on the basis of market condition start accumulating those shares.</li></ul><p>Eg. – If market is high buy very small quantities and at every fall, quantity can be increased.</p><p>Another way is to keep accumulating particular number of shares every day, every week or every month irrespective of condition of the market.</p><p><br></p>','d99138d010d311e9be889d5644b90a10'),(21,'CHAPTER 6',3,6,'4ab602d047f411e9bd5aa3d201dd1bdc','4ab602d047f411e9bd5aa3d201dd1bdc','2019-01-03 10:53:17','2019-03-16 19:34:01','<p><strong>Mutual Funds:</strong></p><p><span style=\"color: black;\">What is a mutual fund? Let\'s explain this term in a very simple way. Let\'s assume that you as an investor have no idea of shares and stocks. You need professional help and expertise. All you have to do is invest in a mutual fund scheme. A mutual fund scheme collects money from investors and buys and sell stocks collectively.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: black;\">Let\'s give you an example Say, there is a Mutual Fund Scheme called ABC Mutual Fund, ABC Asset Management Company. What this fund does it comes out with a new offer of a scheme called ABC Mid Cap Scheme. When it gathers say INR 100 crores, it invests the money gathered from several investors into the stock markets. If the scheme is an equity scheme it would invest most of its money in shares, while if it was a debt scheme it would invest the same in debt like government securities, bonds etc. </span></p><p><span style=\"color: black;\">Now, the fund will offer you units at Rs 10 initially. You buy one unit at Rs 10. Say, you buy 1000 units at Rs 10 and you pay a sum of Rs 10,000. One year down the line the stocks invested by the ABC Mid Cap Fund rise and net asset value (NAV) climbs to Rs 12. You can now sell the units back to the mutual fund at Rs 12 and you would get Rs 12,000 for your 1000 units. </span></p><p><strong style=\"color: black;\">What happens for a new buyer who is interested to buy the units? </strong></p><p><span style=\"color: black;\">For a new buyer who is interested to buy the units he would have to buy the units at Rs 12, since the net asset value has climbed. This means he has to pay Rs 12. In the example above we have tried to make it as simple as possible, assuming that the ABC Mid Cap Fund is an open ended fund. Open ended fund means it can be bought and sold any time. We have avoided writing on things like entry and exit load, so as to avoid confusion. </span></p><p><strong style=\"color: black;\">Types of mutual funds in India </strong></p><p><span style=\"color: black;\">Again, we are trying to make it as simple as possible in explaining to you the different types of mutual funds. </span></p><p><span style=\"color: black;\">1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><strong style=\"color: black;\">Equity Funds</strong></p><p><span style=\"color: black;\">Equity funds invest most of the money that they gather from investors into equity shares. These are high risk schemes and investors can also make losses, since most of the money is parked into shares. These types of schemes are suitable for investors with an appetite for risk.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: black;\">2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><strong style=\"color: black;\">Debt Funds</strong></p><p><span style=\"color: black;\">Debt funds invest most of their money into debt schemes including corporate debt, debt issued by banks, gilts and government securities. These types of funds are suitable for investors who are not willing to take risks. Returns are almost assured in these types of schemes.</span></p><p><strong style=\"color: black;\">3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Balanced funds </strong></p><p><span style=\"color: black;\">Balanced funds invest their money in equity as well as debt. They generally tend to skew the money more into equity then debt. The objective in the end is again to earn superior returns. Of course, they might alter their investment pattern based on market conditions.</span></p><p><strong style=\"color: black;\">4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Money Market </strong><span style=\"color: black;\">Mutual Funds </span></p><p><span style=\"color: black;\">Money market mutual funds are also called Liquid funds. They invest a bulk of their money in safer short-term instruments like Certificates of Deposit, Treasury and Commercial Paper. Most of the investment is for a smaller duration. </span></p><p><strong style=\"color: black;\">5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Gilt Funds</strong></p><p><span style=\"color: black;\">Gilt Funds are perhaps the most secure instruments that are around. They invest bulk of their money in government securities. Since they have backing of the government they are considered the safest mutual fund units around. </span></p><p><strong>How to invest in Mutual Funds</strong></p><p><strong>Lumpsum Investment</strong> – you can invest in Mutual Fund in a lumpsum way where you can put any amount in any selected fund</p><p><strong>Systematic Investment Plan (SIP</strong>) – through SIP you can put any amount starting from INR 500 in any of available funds. That amount mostly gets debited from your Bank account on one particular date and the selected fund will be bought at NAV of that day. SIP period can be monthly, quarterly or half yearly.</p><p><strong>How beginners should start?</strong></p><p>Beginners should start investing through SIP mode where they can start with very small amount and the amount will be debited in small parts. Gradually investor will get to learn about market and can start investing in bulk further.</p><ul><li><strong>Debentures</strong></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">A debenture is one of the most typical forms of long term loans that a company can take.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">It is normally a loan that should be repaid on a specific date, but some debentures are irredeemable securities (sometimes referred to as perpetual debentures).</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">The majority of debentures come with a fixed interest rate. This interest must be paid before dividends are paid to shareholders. In the US, most debentures are unsecured, but elsewhere debentures are typically secured through the borrower’s assets.</span></p><ul><li><strong style=\"color: black;\">Debenture holders</strong></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Debenture holders (investors) are not allowed to vote in the company\'s general shareholders meetings, but they may have separate meetings or votes, for instance regarding changes to the rights associated with the debentures.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">The interest that is paid to debenture holders is calculated as a charge against profit in the company\'s financial statements.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: black;\">Types of debentures</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Debentures come in two types:</span></p><ul><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Convertible debentures:&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Convertible bonds or bonds that can be converted into equity shares of the issuing company after a predetermined period of time. To investors, convertible bonds are more attractive because the bonds can be converted, and to companies they have the advantage that they normally have lower interest rates than non-convertible corporate bonds.</span></li><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Non-convertible debentures:</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">&nbsp;Standard debentures that can\'t be converted into equity shares of the liable company. Since they can\'t be converted, they usually have higher interest rates than convertible debentures.</span></li><li><strong style=\"color: black;\">Benefits</strong></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Debentures are mainly beneficial to companies by having a lower interest rate than other types of loans, e.g. overdrafts. Further, they normally only need to be repaid by a very remote date.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">The main benefits of debentures to investors is that they can usually be sold in stock exchanges quite easily and they come with less risk than e.g. equities.</span></p><ul><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Passive Income Opportunity for Debenture buyers</strong></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">An investor who buys debentures get fixed interest which is better than interest on Fixed Deposit. These investors are the one who don’t like to take risk. These investors don’t like up and down of markets and would like to play safe with their investments. Returns through debentures is secured source of passive income. This product is a for low risk low return category.</span></p><p><br></p>','db59af1010d311e9bcc9b56ae7cc6d58'),(22,'CHAPTER 7',3,7,'a6b191e047f411e9a1982b1ffde72df5','a6b191e047f411e9a1982b1ffde72df5','2019-01-03 10:54:49','2019-03-16 19:36:27','<p><strong style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Passive Income from Real Estate</strong></p><p>Real estate is one of the most lucrative source of passive income. Investment in real estate at right time and at right place can give</p><ul><li><strong>Good appreciation in property vale</strong></li><li><strong>Good passive income in the form of rent</strong></li></ul><p>Real estate is not that liquid and there are huge commissions or stamp duty registrations to be paid for property buying and selling. This opportunity requires lot of study and one cannot blindly invest as the quantity of money required for real estate buying and selling is large.</p><p>Rental is a main source of passive income while investing in property. So calculation of proper return of investment is very important while shortlisting any property. Returns anywhere between 3-5% pa in India are good returns.</p><p>Investor can also take loan to invest in real estate if returns are very lucrative and property loans are cheapest loans available in the market.</p><ul><li><strong>Portfolio Management Services</strong></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68);\">The portfolio is a collection of investment instruments like shares, mutual funds,&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: rgb(2, 116, 190);\">bonds</span><span style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68);\">, fixed deposits and other cash equivalents etc. Portfolio management is the art of selecting the right investment tools in the right proportion to generate optimum returns from the investment made.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68);\">In other words, a portfolio is a group of assets. If compared, generally it is found that the risk attached to an asset is more than the risk of a portfolio. This is because portfolio gives an opportunity to diversify risk.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: rgb(2, 116, 190);\">Diversification</span><span style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68);\">&nbsp;of risk does not mean that risk will be eliminated. With every asset, two types of risk are attached, diversifiable risk and market risk. Even an optimum portfolio cannot eliminate market risk, but can only reduce or eliminate the diversifiable risk. As soon as risk reduces, the variability of return reduces leading to better and assured returns.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68);\">Best portfolio management practice runs on the principle of minimum risk and maximum return within a given time frame. A portfolio is built based on investor’s income, investment budget and risk appetite keeping the expected rate of return in mind.</span></p><ul><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">OBJECTIVES OF PORTFOLIO MANAGEMENT</strong></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68);\">When a portfolio is built, following objectives are to be kept in mind by the portfolio manager based on an individual’s expectation. The choice of one or more of these depends on the investor’s personal preference.</span></p><ul><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68);\">Capital Growth</strong></li><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68);\">Security of Principal Amount Invested</strong></li><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68);\">Liquidity</strong></li><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68);\">Marketability of Securities Invested in</strong></li><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68);\">Diversification of Risk</strong></li><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68);\">Consistent Returns</strong></li><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68);\">Tax Planning</strong></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68);\">Investors hire portfolio managers and avail professional services for the&nbsp;management of portfolio by as paying a pre-decided fee for these services. Let us understanding who is a portfolio manager and tasks involved in the&nbsp;management of a portfolio.</span></p><ul><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">WHO IS A PORTFOLIO MANAGER?</strong></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68);\">Portfolio Manager is a person who understands his client’s investment needs and suggests a suitable investment mix to meet his client’s investment objectives. This tailor-made investment plan is recommended keeping in mind the&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: rgb(2, 116, 190);\">risk-return</span><span style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68);\">&nbsp;balance.</span><strong style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68);\">&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Passive income from Business Empire</strong></li></ul><p>Take example of all the big tycoons – MukeshAmbani, Laxmi Mittal, Bill Gates, Carlos slim Helu&nbsp;- all created business empires. Once business grows at level that systems become autopilot. Than these creators don’t have to look after small day to day operations of business.</p><p>Once business is created in an autopilot mode, we can have excellent passive income from such business operations.</p><p>Even small business like wine shop where owner setup shop and give it for management to manager which keeps giving passive income to owner. There are lot more retail business which operates on same autopilot model which gives good amount of passive income to investor</p><p>There are lot of manufacturing or assembly units which run on the same model which keeps giving passive income to the owner.</p><p>There are many hotels or lodges where we have never seen owner and still it makes lot of income for the owners. These owners at time act as a sleeping partners and invest in the project and give it to someone to handle it. Income is shared with such sleeping partners on shared ratio.</p><p>There are lot of business where either you act as a sleeping partner or owner (and it doesn’t require your time)</p><p>Below is a case study where we tried to explain passive income opportunities from different sources in a single example-</p>','dd15631010d311e9a72c134ca29a96e7');
INSERT INTO `chapters` VALUES (23,'CHAPTER 8',3,8,'e55ea22047f411e98f100dbb430e58eb','e55ea22047f411e98f100dbb430e58eb','2019-01-03 10:59:53','2019-03-16 19:38:18','<p><strong>Create Enterprise for Passive Income</strong></p><p>Kamal has started one company called XYZ who will be in the business of providing digital marketing solutions to corporates. Kamal has initial capital of only INR 2 lakhs and required INR 2 lakhs to start the company. So he borrowed remaining INR 2 lakhs from his friend Rahul @ interest of 2% per month</p><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></p><p><span style=\"background-color: lime;\">Passive Income Opportunity for Rahul – As Kamal is his good friend he didn’t mind giving loan to him at 2 % per month. By doing nothing and with some amount of risk that if Kamal doesn’t return his money he would earn passive income of INR 4000 per month</span></p><p>So the business is started with INR 4L company. XYZ fix expenditure is around INR 80k per month</p><p>Company’s capital when started</p><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></p><p>Within months they got couple of clients and now their income started coming in. The business started flourishing. Company worked quite hard during initial phase and got good set of clients. Revenues started coming in rapidly.</p><p>After a year the company started doing well. Valuation of the company grew to 40 lakhs. Clients started coming in rapidly and now there was a need for more money. There was order which required them big team and big capital. They required further capital of 60 lakhs. So Kamal approached bank for loan but bank found it is too early for them to come and apply for loan. So kamal spoke to some personal contacts and one of his friend’s company got ready to invest in his project. So, ABC company got ready with a term that they needed ownership in the company. Kamal got ready to give them 40% ownership in the company. So now whatever profits will be there 40% will have to be shared with ABC company. This type of investment is called private equity investment</p><p><span style=\"background-color: lime;\">Passive Income Opportunity for ABC Company – By investing in company through private way and by seeing scope in the company ABC got equity/ownership of 40% shares in the company. Such type of investment is called private equity investment. For ABC it is passive income as they will not be involved directly into business operations.&nbsp;</span></p><p>So after 2<sup>nd</sup> year Company’s position was:</p><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></p><p>Company banged on to expansion plans and they started gaining goodwill in the market. Value of the company got increase to 2.2 crores after end of second year. Their clientele started increasing. Scope of digital marketing got saturated where they realized a need to come to different vertical of software development which required further capital requirement of 1 crore.</p><p>XYZ went to bank for loan but still bank was not comfortable giving them loan. Kamal again started meeting different companies. Kamal met one merchant banker who suggested him to issue debentures of the company. They enter into contract with that merchant banker to help them raise capital through debentures of 1 crore.</p><p><span style=\"background-color: aqua;\">Meaning of Debentures - </span><span style=\"background-color: aqua; color: black;\">A debenture is a type of debt instrument that is not secured by&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://www.investopedia.com/terms/p/physicalasset.asp\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: aqua; color: rgb(0, 91, 157);\">physical assets</a><span style=\"background-color: aqua; color: black;\">&nbsp;or&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://www.investopedia.com/terms/c/collateral.asp\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: aqua; color: rgb(0, 91, 157);\">collateral</a><span style=\"background-color: aqua; color: black;\">. Debentures are backed only by the general creditworthiness and reputation of the issuer. Both corporations and governments frequently issue this type of bond to secure capital. Like other types of bonds, debentures are documented in an&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://www.investopedia.com/terms/i/indenture.asp\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: aqua; color: rgb(0, 91, 157);\">indenture</a><span style=\"background-color: aqua; color: black;\">. Debentures have no collateral. Bond buyers generally purchase debentures based on the belief that the bond issuer is unlikely to default on the repayment. An example of a government debenture would be any government-issued&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://www.investopedia.com/terms/t/treasurybond.asp\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: aqua; color: rgb(0, 91, 157);\">Treasury bond (T-bond)</a><span style=\"background-color: aqua; color: black;\">&nbsp;or&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://www.investopedia.com/terms/t/treasurybill.asp\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: aqua; color: rgb(0, 91, 157);\">Treasury bill (T-bill).</a><span style=\"background-color: aqua; color: black;\">&nbsp;T-bonds and T-bills are generally considered risk free because governments, at worst, can print off more money or raise taxes to pay these types of debts.</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: aqua; color: black;\">Debentures are the most common form of long-term loans that can be taken out by a corporation. These loans are repayable on a fixed date and pay a fixed rate of interest. A company normally makes these interest payments prior to paying out dividends to its&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://www.investopedia.com/terms/s/shareholder.asp\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: aqua; color: rgb(0, 91, 157);\">shareholders</a><span style=\"background-color: aqua; color: black;\">, similar to most debt instruments. In relation to other types of loans and debt instruments, debentures are advantageous in that they carry a lower interest rate and have a repayment date that is far in the future.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: black;\">So company issued bond to raise INR 10000000 @ 12% per annum from market</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: lime;\">Passive Income Opportunity for Debenture owners – Anybody who buy debentures of company will earn @ 12% per annum. These type of investors prefer some fixed returns against their investment. They expect returns more than Fixed Deposit with banks and that is the reason they carry certain amount of risk</span></p><p><span style=\"color: black;\">After raising funds through debentures – end of 3</span><sup style=\"color: black;\">rd</sup><span style=\"color: black;\"> year, companies position:</span></p><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></p><p>Company did extremely well after 3<sup>rd</sup> year, sales boosted because of good product penetration. Quality of team was excellent. Owner’s had a board meeting where they decided to go in full flow for next 2 years. So next 2 year company recruited team’s from competition with few more product mix. Company planned to expand in USA and European Market after 5 years where they required good amount of funds. After 5 years’ company’s valuation was around 19 crores and company needed around 11 crores for expansion in foreign markets. Again company went to bank and they got ready to give loan of only INR 3 crores which was not going to help out. Kamal met merchant banker again who suggested him to raise money by giving shares to general public and raise capital from the market. So he suggested to raise money through IPO.</p><p><span style=\"background-color: yellow;\">Meaning of IPO - </span><span style=\"background-color: yellow; color: black;\">An initial public offering (IPO) is the first time that the stock of a&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://www.investopedia.com/terms/p/privatecompany.asp\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: yellow; color: rgb(0, 91, 157);\">private company</a><span style=\"background-color: yellow; color: black;\">&nbsp;is offered to the public. IPOs are often issued by smaller, younger companies seeking capital to expand, but they can also be done by large&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://www.investopedia.com/terms/p/privately-owned.asp\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: yellow; color: rgb(0, 91, 157);\">privately owned</a><span style=\"background-color: yellow; color: black;\">&nbsp;companies looking to become publicly traded. In an IPO, the&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://www.investopedia.com/terms/i/issuer.asp\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: yellow; color: rgb(0, 91, 157);\">issuer</a><span style=\"background-color: yellow; color: black;\">&nbsp;obtains the assistance of an&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://www.investopedia.com/terms/u/underwriting.asp\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: yellow; color: rgb(0, 91, 157);\">underwriting</a><span style=\"background-color: yellow; color: black;\">&nbsp;firm, which helps determine what type of security to issue, the best&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://www.investopedia.com/terms/o/offeringprice.asp\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: yellow; color: rgb(0, 91, 157);\">offering price</a><span style=\"background-color: yellow; color: black;\">, the amount of shares to be issued and the time to bring it to market.</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: yellow; color: black;\">Through IPO capital is raised through book building process where anyone from open public feels that XYZ company is doing quite good and expanding and there are chances that if he invest in that company his capital will rise as the company grows. Normally each share is given for Rs. 10 which is called face value of share. Ad XYZ is already doing good business and expanding they give shares to open public at premium. So normal investor has to pay face value + premium = Bid/Offer Price. Bid and offer price is the price between which investor gets his shares.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: black;\">Companies position before raising money from market after 5 years:</span></p><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></p><p><span style=\"color: black;\">In XYZ example suppose company decided to approach merchant banker to help them raise capital through IPO. Which is said to be company raising funds from primary market. Company decided to give 40% shares to public. From which Kamal will give 20% and ABC will give 20%. Suppose company has initially issued 1000000 shares.</span></p><p>Company got very good response from investors in open market and raised good money through IPO. In fact IPO got oversubscribed by 5 times (Over subscription means if there is demand to sell 4 lakh shares in primary market and 20 lakhs applications have come to issue shares). So after Book building process and giving shares to public XYZ company will look like:</p><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: yellow;\">Equity Share or stock meaning – </strong></p><p><span style=\"background-color: yellow; color: rgb(66, 65, 66);\">Equity shares are the main source of finance of a firm. It is issued to the general public. Equity share­holders do not enjoy any preferential rights with regard to repayment of capital and dividend. They are entitled to residual income of the company, but they enjoy the right to control the affairs of the business and all the shareholders collectively are the owners of the company.</span></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: yellow; color: rgb(66, 65, 66);\">The main features of equity shares are:&nbsp;</strong></p><p><span style=\"background-color: yellow; color: rgb(66, 65, 66);\">1. They are permanent in nature.</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: yellow; color: rgb(66, 65, 66);\">2. Equity shareholders are the actual owners of the company and they bear the highest risk.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: yellow; color: rgb(66, 65, 66);\">3. Equity shares are transferable, i.e. ownership of equity shares can be transferred with or without consideration to other person.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: yellow; color: rgb(66, 65, 66);\">4. Dividend payable to equity shareholders is an appropriation of profit.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: yellow; color: rgb(66, 65, 66);\">5. Equity shareholders do not get fixed rate of dividend.</span></p><p>Now suppose Raju has applied to buy 100 shares of XYZ through IPO and got 20 shares as the IPO got oversubscribed by 5 times. As per valuation he would get share for RS. 290 from primary market.</p><p>Before going for book building process and raise money through IPO XYZ has to do lot of formalities. It has to take permission from SEBI who is regulatory body formed to safeguard interest of investors in India. Also they have to give application to list on exchange where shares of XYZ will get traded. XYZ is given a date where it will be listed on secondary market i.e. stock markets like NSE &amp; BSE for trading. So if investors miss out to buy shares of XYZ through IPO they can buy it from secondary market as well.</p><p>Once the share will get listed on exchange it will get open for general public for trading henceforth. If demand for XYZ is very high is secondary market as well it will open much above than the bought price of INR 290 in primary market. But if people feel that the growth of XYZ is not that much they will not buy share in secondary market and share might open at a rate lower than primary market.</p><p>We will assume that public sentiment for XYZ is very positive because of growth story of XYZ, then share will open at much higher price. Suppose shares open at 10% higher than price from primary market i.e. 290 + 29 = 319 than investor in secondary market will get this share for INR 319. And once who bought this share in primary market for 290 can sell it at 10 % profit.</p><p>This is beauty of stock market. It is demand and supply game which investors have to predict and act upon. Also equity share holders get profits of the company in the form of dividends.</p><p><span style=\"background-color: lime;\">Passive Income Opportunity for Equity share owners – Equity Market is a huge market where lot of passive income could be earned. Timing to enter into stock and prediction about future is very important before investing into stock market. If it goes wrong, may result into huge losses. Just imagine someone or en</span><span style=\"background-color: green;\">t</span><span style=\"background-color: lime;\">ire company works for you day and night to make you rick. They launch new products, do sales, make strategies, do requirement just to make you rich. That is the power of share investment. Then you buy it through IPO or stock exchanges it doesn’t matter. Equity share holders also get share of profits of the company in the form of dividend</span></p><p>In above example just imagine how rich would Kamal be if stock trades for INR 350. He would be sitting on capital of INR 400000 x 350 = 140000000 a guy who started with a base capital of INR 200000.</p><p>This case study is hypothetical but there are lot of things which can be noticed.</p><p>Rahul who shared at very first stage when the company was too small still get interest at fixed rate or may be little bit more if interest rate is raised a bit. He seems to be a very conservative investor who is happy with fixed but safe investment</p><p>ABC company which enter in earlier stage got huge appreciation in capital as they had taken risk in newly started up company which was showing sign of great growth. They participated at every level in the growth of company and are one of the major beneficiaries in the growth story of the company. Point to note that if something goes wrong with the company, they will be major losers as well. Since they hold equity that means they are direct beneficiaries of profits as well as loses.</p><p>Like Rahul, debenture owners also get returns on some fixed rate. They are also conserviate investors who prefers to invest money on interest with some company at higher rate than with bank at lower interest rate. In such a wonderful growth story, even their returns of investment is fixed to the interest rate which was decided.</p><p>Share holders are ultimate beneficiaries of growth of company. They require to study hard on what should be the entry level and exit level of the company. Share owners get maximum benefit on growth story of the company. Share investment is ultimate source of passive income as investor gets appreciation as well as dividends (share of profits).</p>','dea4f59010d311e9bac6eb1c80342274'),(24,'CHAPTER 9',3,9,'0a71d5f047f511e99b92f3a72e6d7e75','0a71d5f047f511e99b92f3a72e6d7e75','2019-01-03 11:01:39','2019-03-16 19:39:43','<p><strong>Case Study 2</strong></p><p>Let’s take same company but now look from another angle</p><p>We will see it from the point of view of Kamal:</p><p>A normal guy with small domain starting a business in a small way.</p><p>When he started he had a capital of only 4 lakhs and from that also he had INR 2 lakhs borrowed money.</p><p>Step 1 he did is hire good digital marketing execution guy, 2 sales guys and 1 back office guys. So he had fixed cost of around INR 80K to start a show. He required capital of 4 lakhs initially as back cost of 5 months. Sales guys bought in some small orders and he concentrated on bigger tickets. And business started flowing in.</p><p>Even before actual business started he had a plan that once his company reaches 1 crore he will make his business auto pilot by recruiting required staff. He rather focused on to bring big investor where he can setup software development company as well.</p><p>That is how in a routine going activities he bought in ABC company to invest with them and the company reaches 1 crore. He than decided to recruit a CEO and handed over operations to him. He than focused on just strategies and development. He would discuss his estimates with CEO who would execute his plans in a way required. Than whatever happened was an autopilot activity with Kamal mostly involved in networking or board meetings.</p><p>This is a hypothetical situation and real life activities are not that simple. But this case study was to make you realize that there are 4 professions where you find people working:</p><ul><li><strong>Profession 1 – Salaried Employee</strong></li><li>This is a working class believe only in active income.</li><li>They know money could be earned only by working hard.</li><li>So in above case studies whatever execution work was shown was actually done by these salaried people.</li><li>They work very hard so that people like Kamal get rich.</li><li>They don’t like to take risks and rather prefer to help someone achieve his dreams.</li><li>They have dreams but they don’t take actions to achieve it.</li><li>They belong to category B</li><li>They earn active income in the form of salary</li><li>They are subjected to highest tax rates</li><li>They can be fired whenever needed</li><li><strong>Profession 2 – Self Employed</strong></li></ul><p>In above case imagine if Kamal wanted to run everything on his own, what would had been a result? It was not possible to grow beyond 1 point.</p><ul><li>Most of self employed people think that they know it all.</li><li>They do everything on their own – sales, marketing, finance, BD etc.</li><li>Once they are sick or not well for few days – business is impacted. They cannot leave their business even for a day.</li><li>They always find themselves rattled between financial things – so it becomes very difficult for them to grow beyond a point.</li><li>They might have to work 24 by 7</li><li><strong>Profession 3 – Investor</strong></li><li>This category is smart and knows how to earn from others effort.</li><li>They love to make money from others work.</li><li>They rather would love to spend time on studying different opportunities.</li><li>They travel across globe and get lot of exposure</li><li>Their money work for them</li><li>Their money work 24 by 7 for them</li><li>People from other categories work for them</li><li>They work hard to find out best investment opportunities available in the market</li><li><strong>Profession 4 -&nbsp;Big Business Enterprise</strong></li><li>They own businesses and create autopilot systems</li><li>They don’t need to present all the time in business</li><li>In above example Kamal belongs to this category</li><li>They make their money work 24 by 7</li><li>They are expert in hiring and nurturing talent</li><li>They know how to make people work for them</li><li>They are excellent in creating systems</li><li>They create process and help talent to follow their path</li></ul><p>In above case study you can identify who is Big business owner, who is investor, who is employee and who is self employed.</p><ul><li><strong>EMPLOYEE &amp; SELF EMPLOYEE – Group B</strong></li><li><strong>Big Business Owner and Investors – Group A</strong></li></ul><p>What all big shots like Donald Trump, Bill Gates, Jeff Bezos Mark Zuckerberg have done and which category the belong to? – They have created a system, hired a talent and made these systems autopilot. They are Big Business Owners</p><p>Who are Warren Buffet, George Soros, Carl Icahn – They are very big investors who work day in day out to find out best available investment opportunities across the globe. They know how to make other business and big enterprises work for them</p><p>We middle class either belong to ‘EMPLOYEE CATEGORY’ or ‘SELF EMPLOYEED CATEGORY’</p><p>I don’t need to ask now which category of profession you want to be into?</p>','e0a3783010d311e996d2d15d95456c3c'),(25,'CHAPTER 1',4,1,'5aefdb1047f511e9a419418edeb15faf','5aefdb1047f511e9a419418edeb15faf','2019-01-03 11:03:10','2019-03-16 19:41:45','<p>In this ARENA the word networking means the network of people we are surrounded by or the type of people we know and interact with in our day to day life.</p><p>All the three ARENA’s:</p><p>Mindset</p><p>Spending Habits</p><p>&amp; passive income</p><p>..is directly or indirectly connected to this ARENA of network.</p><p>As already explained thoroughly, our mindset is the result of environment we live in where we can also say that our mindset is determined by the network we deal with in our day to day life. If we surround our self with negative toxic people, obviously our mindset will be negative and toxic.</p><p>If we surround our self with positive and successful people our mindset will be positive and work towards success. So basically the network we live in, is very important for our success in all aspects of life.</p><p>Spending time with people who are financially successful will have great impact on our financial position. We can learn about their patterns or where they spend their money which will give us exposure out of our imagination. Which will lead to spending our time and money on things which can give us great amount of income.</p><p>Tones of passive income ideas can be generated from the network we are part of. Rich and successful people obviously have multiple sources of passive income and being in circle of those people will give us lot of learning opportunities on how to create it.</p><p>Ultimately our financial success is the product of network of people we deal with, day in day out.</p><p>If you are not fortunate enough to have financial success in your life – just try to experiment and see the quality of people you deal with every day. We are sure that you will be among the network of people who are not fortunate enough to taste financial success. There are chances from outside they might seem to have achieved great financial success but if you go little bit inside their life, you will come to know that they are not that successful as they pertain to be.</p><p>And if you are financially doing good in life, you will be surprised to see that you are surrounded by financially successful people</p><p>We repeat it once again, ‘WE ARE PRODUCT OF NETWORK OF PEOPLE WE ARE SURROUNDED WITH’</p><p><strong>Let’s learn what one drops of poison can do to whole jug of water?</strong></p><p>What will happen if we mix one drop of poison in a big jug of purified water. Yes, you are right. It will make whole water poisonous. Even than you boil that water 1 time, 2 times or 3 times – that water has become poisonous. The effect of poison will only lessen once we mix more and more water. And at one point the effect of poison will vanish completely.</p><p>So it should be learned that whatever positivity we have in our life can be destroyed by 1 toxic guy in our life who can be our friend, our relative, father, mother anyone. In case of friends we can still think of getting rid of them but we cannot do same with our family. In that situation it becomes very difficult for us to maintain that type of positivity. The solution for that is spend lesser time than normal with that toxic guy in our life and surround ourselves with even more positive network. The result will be the negativity we inherit from all the toxic elements will vanish gradually. Not only that it will make that toxic element in our life much more positive by seeing positive changes in our life.</p><p>There are people who face lot of negativity in life because of circumstances. They are stuck financially, going through some very depressing times, facing some family problems, or encountered some great loss recently or may be some other reason - whatever we have covered till now will go completely out of their mind. Just try to remain in their shoes for a minute and we will get to know the reason how difficult it will be for them to even understand what we are talking about?</p><p>The only solution we have for such people is to change their network or circle of people they live with, completely. Select vibrant, effective and positive people around you and best way to do that is join some good religious group who talk a lot about positive effective things or some laughter group or some other networking group who encourage people.</p><p>It is important to change network, if you are going though any depressing situation in life without which any ARENA we talk about is of no use. Once you change your network you will start noticing all positive changes across you. This is no rocket science. One drop of poison will not have any impact on river or in fact it will make a drop of poison a part of its puritys</p>','e87245e010d311e991ae89e254d4909e'),(26,'CHAPTER 2',4,2,'7bfec0f047f511e9aca7e1754c607b01','7bfec0f047f511e9aca7e1754c607b01','2019-01-03 11:06:31','2019-03-16 19:42:28','<p><strong>How to involve yourself with people</strong></p><p>Obviously there is a question which would have come to your mind on how should you involve yourself with people. Before coming to answer of this question, lets us tell you that Human being is a social animal. If Human is thrown in a room alone for 10 years without any amenities and learning mechanism in that room, we will find him just like an animal without any features of normal human being. Languages, antiquates, behavior are human activates created by human himself. So human has to learn continuously for which they require to be in network. In fact, anyone who is not in good network of other people, is outdated. And their tendency to learn stops.</p><p>How can you expect anyone with limited capacity to learn, perform well financially? So to do well financially you have to be among the network of people. Let’s understand the fact which we are trying to emphasize on that human being have to be in network to grow. But our ego plays very good role in not allowing us to engage with other people. You might want to start conversation with someone who can be a very good contact but there are 3 great barriers which will stop you in doing so. Those barriers are:</p><ul><li><strong>EGO</strong></li><li><strong>SHAME</strong></li><li><strong>FEAR OF REJECTION</strong></li></ul><p>You might not start conversation with always a question – why should I start a conversation? If you really want to grow well financially you have to throw this great word – EGO in your toilet and move out. Than only will you be able to start a conversation and involve yourself with other people.</p><p>Shame is something which is just deep inside our mind and so is a fear of rejection. What will happen if we start conversation with anyone? Believe us that person will not kill us if we start conversation. But if we start conversation there are chances for us to get into one new circle of network and there are good chances of us to grow financially.</p><p>Today as an exercise – try to speak to at least 5 new people. Believe us it is not that difficult.</p><p>Once you are able to do it today – lets take a task to speak to 5 new people every day for a month. Try to build relationship to the level that at least you can share your contact details. One again we are repeating as it is most important – The more network you have, the more probability of you to become financially successful.</p><p><strong>How to start conversation</strong></p><p>Let us give you few ideas on how exactly to start conversation:</p><p>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;People love compliments – You can start any conversation with small complements like:</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Nice shirt</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Nice watch</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Nice book</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Nice speech</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Nice voice</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Or anything</p><p>Compliments are very difficult to forget. Ever imagined why people post so many pictures on Facebook or other social media? They want more likes J</p><p>They want compliments. So, it is best way to start conversation with anyone, with small compliments</p><p>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Another way to start conversation is through existing link. If you are really keen to start conversation with someone, you can start with reference. It will be very easy to start plus chances of sound conversation will be great if you start with some reference</p><p><strong>Few ideas on how to make your network very strong</strong></p><p>Let us repeat once again – OUR FINANCIAL SUCCESS IS DIRECTLY PROPERTIONATE TO THE TYPE OF NETWORK WE HAVE.</p><p>We have to make our network very very strong which should be our prime agenda. If your phone doesn’t ring at least 50 times a day – we are not a good networker. People don’t like to speak to you.</p><p>Here we are giving few ideas’ on how to make your network very strong:</p><p>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Be a good listener – Please put this thing deep inside your mind that everybody loves to speak. And there are very few people who love to listen. Good listeners are liked by lot of people since there is scarcity of those type of people. So listening quality can make you hero among different groups you are part of. Moreover, listening will help you to learn new things from perspective of people speaking to you.</p><p>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Join some networking group – There are sites like meetup.com where you get chance to meet people of your hobbies or interest. If you are looking for some business contacts – BNI is one of the best network to join. Joining those networks are quite easy and you would be able to make bulk contacts at a time. We strongly recommended to join meetup.com right today. If you are in business, we will strongly recommend to join some successful chapter of BNI. You will not regret this decision and we can vouch on our words.</p><p>3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Join Religious groups – Lot of successful people believe in work life balance and they are majorly found associated with some or other religious group. We are not asking you to make contacts because of some selfish purpose. Always make contacts or network without any expectation of actual business and than only you will be able to make best use of your contacts</p><p>4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Hobbies – Everybody has some hobbies and we strongly recommend never to leave your hobbies. If you like music we strongly recommend to join some local music community. There are 2 reason:</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;One is that hobbies are always stress buster and can give you lot of relaxation</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Second is that you will find lot of like minded people where you can chat freely and associate for a long lasting time</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>','e9f55fa010d311e9b61263902acde99e'),(27,'CHAPTER 3',4,3,'8bc3350047f511e989fc851b3b503a14','8bc3350047f511e989fc851b3b503a14','2019-01-03 11:07:16','2019-03-16 19:42:51','<p><strong>Case Study</strong></p><p>We will have small case study to explain how good network can help anyone financially?</p><p>Raj is a well known guy in a town who got very good network. He is known by lot of people since he is very good in networking. All the big business people of town knows him. Raj has recently completed his interior designing course and planned to start his own designing studio. He made wonderful office and invited all well known people of town for inauguration.</p><p>Everybody appreciated work of his office. Since he has good network there is a friend – Vijay who is big diamond merchant who recently bought new office. He called Raj to discuss plans for his office and the deal was finalized without even discussing budget as they got very good relation. Raj made good profit out of that.</p><p>One of friend of Vijay visited his office and liked interior work a lot. Vijay called up Raj to meet his friend and Raj got deal for his friend as well.</p><p>The same way Raj made good use of his contact to develop his business and is one of renowned name in the market now.</p><p>There are lot of interior designers in his town who are struggling even for a single work and Raj has tones of work. Nobody discusses budgeting with him since he is renowned name. Moreover, getting work done through Raj in itself is a brand now.</p><p>Tell us – what played a major role in Raj’s progress??</p><p>His work – to some extent but more importantly it was his network which got him to enter offices of well known people. Once you are associated with well know guy – there are chances you will become well known guy because you are being referred by well known guy.</p><p>So we hope above case study made you clear how important networking is in our financial life</p>','eb8db1c010d311e9a6edd962da4fdf07'),(28,'CHAPTER 4',4,4,'96b04e3047f511e9be531b7e1a4b8443','96b04e3047f511e9be531b7e1a4b8443','2019-01-03 11:09:48','2019-03-16 19:43:19','<p><strong>Networking and passive income:</strong></p><p>Passive income opportunities will not come to you by sitting at home. It will come from your network. Number of opportunities of passive income is directly proportionate to the type, quality and number of networks you are surrounded by.</p><p>You will automatically start getting opportunities if you surround yourself with good network of people and believe us it will come in abundance. There will be different type of people you will find in your network:</p><ul><li>Some require funds to grow</li><li>Some require helping hands</li><li>Some might require solutions</li><li>Some might require strategies</li><li>Some might require manpower</li><li>Some might require space</li></ul><p>Etc</p><p>There are good chances you might have what your network is looking for? Which will create either Active Income Opportunity or passive Income Opportunity. It will be upon you what you are looking for? And you expect opportunities to come to you automatically by sitting at home or without any network – you are just wasting your time.</p><p>Friends there are unlimited opportunities and most of them are of passive nature – it is just we have to surround over self with those opportunities and gather as many as we can.</p><p>Lastly, we will conclude with a statement that ‘Opportunities will come only when you speak’</p><p>Rightly said <strong><em>‘BAAT KARNE SE HI BAAT BANTI HAI’.</em></strong></p><p>Here we conclude with all the four ARENAS.</p><p>We strongly recommend to go through each topic in sequence. Don’t jump to next topic till the time you have completed and practiced earlier topic.</p><p>Let us repeat once again – Gaining financial success or getting into group A is not one-day affair but a continuous practice required.</p><p>All these ARENAS are to be crossed over a period of time. You have to decided your time frame. If you really want to grow fast financially practice these ARENAS ‘Day in Day out’.</p><p>If you are associated with something and are not able to give sufficient time to the ARENAS we have discussed – start moving towards it and you will start seeing changes in life.</p><p>This is very clear that these ARENAS are well researched methods to reach financial success and we are very sure that anyone with even bit of energy can achieve greatness in financial life once they cross all 4 ARENAS.</p><p>We wish you a lot of Financial Success in your life.</p><p><strong><em>You can reach us at </em></strong><a href=\"mailto:info@yoovaventures.com\" target=\"_blank\"><strong><em>info@yoovaventures.com</em></strong></a><strong><em> for any queries</em></strong></p><p><br></p>','ed31a75010d311e9a60ab978f3898ad1');
