INSERT INTO `modules` VALUES (1,'MINDSET ARENA','<p>Right from the first breath we take, we start cultivating our mindset. It keeps developing every second. There is the range of mindset between which a person lives his life. It varies from person to person. People from ‘Group A’ who are already rich have broad &amp; rich mindset whereas people from ‘Group B’ have very narrow &amp; limited mindset.</p><p>Group A people see the world from a different perspective. They believe in changing the world the way they want. They are always positive because they always think positive. They think big. They think of creating employment for large number of people. Self and family security hardly matters for them. They are not scared of taking risks. For them not taking risk is the biggest risk.</p><p>Since their mindset is broad, they think broad and get all the ideas from the world and execute it. To execute their ideas, they need people, so they recruit them from ‘Group B’. As people from ‘Group B’ have a very narrow mindset and are scared to take risk, they prefer to work for people from ‘Group A’ and help them execute their ideas.</p><p>Since mindset of people in ‘Group A’ is big, their houses are big, their cars are big, their lifestyle is high profile, their stature in society is high. They travel the globe.&nbsp;</p><p>On the other hand, people in Group B see the world in a way people from group A wants them to see it. Group B people have a very small and poor mindset. Group B people are always scared. Their mind is stuck between work, family security, owned house and routine expenses. They hardly take chances and that is the reason they don’t get opportunities. They work for people in Group A and feel pride with their performance and loyalty they show for people in Group A. Most people in Group B are stuck financially in such a way that they spoil their creativity to think beyond their routine jobs. They become slave of how their lives take them. They hardly travel places across globe. Their mindset just rotates around their jobs, work, family and small social life.</p><p>So it is easy to understand that it is impossible to move from Group B to Group A unless we change our mindset. Let’s accept the fact that we human beings are slaves of our mind and we should treat it like a KING. Our mind is a king and our mindset is the kingdom.</p><p>Now let’s decide, where you want to live?</p><p>In a Prosperous or a Poor kingdom?</p><p>Let’s try to find out how our mindset develops – As a kid our mindset is at peak. As our mindset is strong, we are hardly scared of anything. When we were kids, if someone would have asked us to reach the top of the sky, we would have certainly tried as there was nothing called failure in our dictionary. As we grow old, our mindset starts developing and in this process our families play the most important role. If our family is conservative our mindset becomes conservative and develops in a conservative way. If our family is open minded, our mindset develops in a same way. THAT IS WHY OUR MINDSET IS A REPLICA OF THE MINDSET OF OUR FAMILY. If your family earns $ 1000, your mindset will remain in the range of 1000’s.&nbsp;If your family earns $ 100000 your mindset will always think in range of $ 100000’s.</p><p>If you are born in a middle-class family with monthly income of $ 2000 and someone asks you to earn $ 1 million next month, will our mind accept this challenge? Certainly not. What if the same challenge is thrown to a guy whose family earns more than $ 10 million a month? His mind will accept it easily. This is how our mindset starts cultivating.</p><p>Further when we start growing, we are encountered with the environment around us. Gradually our mindset starts taking shape of that environment. Our mindset takes the shape of the school we study, friends we have, clubs we go, academy we join, activities we do; Every damn thing impacts our mindset.</p><p>Let us see if we can change our mindset from small &amp; restricted to big &amp; open ones?</p><p>Roman Abramovich, owner of Chelsa Football Club having net worth of around 8.2 billion, was born in poverty.</p><p>Steel tycoon Lakshmi Mittal having net worth of around 12.2 billion was born in a poor family in India.</p><p>Sheldon Adelson was the son of a cab driver and now the owner of the largest Casino in the world.</p><p>There are a lot more similar stories. Bill Gates, Mark Zuckerberg, Jack Ma were all born in ordinary families and are now few of the richest names on earth.</p><p>These people though born in poor families didn’t allow their mindset to be impacted. They chose to control the environment around them. We cannot control the family we are born in but we can certainly control the environment around us.</p><p>That is why Bill Gates said, <em style=\"color: rgb(24, 24, 24);\">“If you are born poor it’s not your mistake, but if you die poor it’s your mistake.”</em></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(24, 24, 24);\">Let us tell you that changing your mindset is not a one-day affair. It requires regular practise and drastic change in the environment you live in.</span></p><p><br></p>',1,'2019-01-03 13:10:16','2018-12-29 19:12:13'),(2,'SPENDING PATTERN','<p>Let’s understand the fact that money is earned to spend. Every individual born on earth wants to have maximum benefit out of each earned penny by spending it. Few people spend it immediately, some save it with a view to spend it later &amp; the later invest it to buy assets and make more money out of it.</p><p>Money has got magical power that it rotates from one hand to another, from one bank account to another. Basically it has to be spent. Either it is spent on something which increases in value or something which decreases in value. At the same time, it can be spent on something which gives you more money or something which starts taking your money. But the important point is money is to be spent.</p><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></p><p>There is difference in spending habits of people in ‘Group A’ &amp; people in ‘Group B’. It is very important to understand and follow it if you are really keen to move to Group A.</p><p><strong>Spending preference of Group B people (in order):</strong></p><p>Taxes, Necessity, Home (on loan), Repayment of loan, Family, Rent, Shopping, Entertainment, Travel, Studies, Health &amp; Insurance</p><p>If money is left: Savings, business, Investments, Donation</p><p><strong>They don’t know how to invest in talent</strong></p><p><strong>Spending preference of Group A people (in order):</strong></p><p>Investments, Business, Health &amp; Insurance, Talent, Studies, Properties (as an investment), Home (they have multiple), Shopping, Travel, Entertainment, Holidays, Donation, taxes</p><p>They don’t save, they invest.</p><p>They don’t have to think of necessities as they have it in abundance.</p><p>They find smart ways of saving tax and pay it after spending on all required things.</p><p>They take loan only to buy more assets (Investments)</p><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></p><p>People in Group A spend their money:</p><ul><li><strong>To buy assets</strong></li><li><strong>Buy businesses</strong></li><li><strong>Hire talent</strong></li><li><strong>On knowledge</strong></li><li><strong>Other investments</strong></li></ul><p>Whatever returns they get from those investments they spend it back on assets. That is how rich grow richer and richer. Part of their returns they spend to buy home, shopping, travel, luxuries, entertainment, holidays, donation. Thus their bank accounts and wallet grows thicker and thicker.</p><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(24, 24, 24);\">How to change spending pattern - Ideally major part of your regular income should be invested as a first preference and rest of the money could be used for other expenses. If you are messed up financially and your expenses are more than your income, then there is a need to have additional avenue for income. In next ARENA we will explain more about avenues of income. Our objective here is to make you understand what are the spending patterns of people in category B who struggle financially. It can’t be changed overnight but can be changed over a period</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(24, 24, 24);\">Another important question is where to invest? There are different assets available in the market which can either build wealth for you or create regular income. We would suggest you spend good amount of time to study different avenues available in the market for investment.</span></p><p><br></p>',2,'2019-01-03 21:10:49','2018-12-29 19:12:31'),(3,'PASSIVE INCOME','<p><span style=\"color: rgb(24, 24, 24);\">If you have ever noticed, People in Group A never work for money, money works for them. They play golf, go for vacations, attend meetings, go for horse race and still they earn money out of our imagination. How is this possible? What type of income is that?</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(24, 24, 24);\">Group B people have always learned that income can only be earned through our hard-work. Like if we don’t go for job, how will we get paid? If we are owner of some retail shop and if we don’t go to shop, how will we make profits? If we are manufacturers of some product and we don’t go to the workshop, how will things be managed?</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(24, 24, 24);\">Is it possible to earn money without actually working for it? Yes, it is actually possible and people in Group A rely mainly on that source of income. That income is called passive income. </span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(24, 24, 24);\">It means an income for which you don’t have to work directly. You have to create a financial plan or work out a financial structure where there is no need for you to look into the day-to-day activities of the entity; still it gives you regular monthly income. This income is called passive income. </span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(24, 24, 24);\">To earn passive income:</span></p><ul><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(24, 24, 24);\">You don’t need to go to office</strong></li><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(24, 24, 24);\">You don’t need to work 9-to-6</strong></li><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(24, 24, 24);\">You don’t need to be physically present in an office/ business establishment</strong></li><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(24, 24, 24);\">You don’t need to open a shop or an office</strong></li><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(24, 24, 24);\">You don’t need to report to anyone</strong></li></ul><p>You earn it, whether you work for it or not.</p><p>Few examples of Passive Income?</p><ul><li><strong>Income earned through rent from the property you own</strong></li><li><strong>Dividend received from the invested stocks</strong></li><li><strong>Interest on fixed deposit</strong></li><li><strong>Interest from bonds</strong></li><li><strong>Profits received from the business you are acting as a sleeping/ silent partner</strong></li><li><strong>Royalty received from the book you have written</strong></li><li><strong>Profits received from the blog you have written</strong></li><li><strong>Income earned from the pictures you clicked and posted on some business site</strong></li><li><strong>Income earned from the app you have developed</strong></li><li><strong>Profits earned from the website you have created</strong></li><li><strong>Profits earned as a promoter of the company you have formed being managed by an appointed CEO</strong></li><li><strong>Profits earned from chain created in Multi Level Management company</strong></li></ul><p>These are just the few common ways of earning passive income. You would say that you have to work for writing a book or blog or for creating an app.</p><p><em>Any such work where you have to work for a limited period, to generate the necessary financial structure and which doesn’t require your full time availability is considered as a passive income.</em> So when you write a book or a blog or create an app, you work for while and later your product will keep earning money for you without your intervention.</p><p>The power of passive income is so strong that it can change your lifestyle completely. In your friend circle or family circle try to find out someone who has passive income and see his/her lifestyle. At the same time, try to find out someone who has only active income (income earned through direct work) and see his/her lifestyle. You will be surprised to see huge lifestyle difference, such as:</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;One with a passive income often goes for vacations and on the other hand, one with only active income keeps working day and night to earn it.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;One with a passive income can party every day whereas one with only active income sleeps early so that he can go back to work on time next day</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;One with passive income has lot of friends or circle as he/she gets enough time to network whereas one with only active income is left with limited circle</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;One with passive income gets lot of time to read, learn and explore new things whereas one with only active income is stuck in routine activities</p><p>Please note that without good source of Passive Income it is not possible to reach Group A. People in Group B either don’t have knowledge on how to earn passive income or they don’t know sources to earn passive income.</p><p>Hard work is required for active income and smart work &amp; some home work is required for passive income. The best for someone starting their career to earn passive income is to start investing in quality assets as soon as they start working. Investment in quality assets give regular passive income and also create wealth.</p><p>People in ‘Group A’ love other people to work for them and they are always alert on any good opportunity created. E.g. – If some ABC company in retail sector doing excellent business. ABC company opening new shops every month, their turnover is increasing, their clients are increasing, their brand value is growing and they have excellent future plans. People in Group A wait for such types of opportunities and would want to take advantage of the business ABC company does. What they will do, they will busy shares of ABC company and thus become owner of the company. In the sense they can earn part of the profits earned by ABC company without actually doing anything. This is just an example of how passive income could be earned without actually doing anything.</p><p><br></p>',3,'2019-01-03 13:12:48','2018-12-29 19:12:54'),(4,'NETWORKING','<p><span style=\"color: rgb(24, 24, 24);\">Human is a </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(24, 24, 24);\">social animal who cannot live &amp; survive</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(24, 24, 24);\"> alone. </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(24, 24, 24);\">Human need to network. </strong><span style=\"color: rgb(74, 74, 74);\">Being connected is paramount for success in the 21</span><sup style=\"color: rgb(74, 74, 74);\">st</sup><span style=\"color: rgb(74, 74, 74);\">&nbsp;century.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(74, 74, 74);\">Unfortunately, business and success is undoubtedly about whom you know, not what you know.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(74, 74, 74);\">Let us tell you very straight without networking it is not possible to reach Group A. In fact, you will find Group A people surrounded by lot of positive people around them. </span></p><p><strong style=\"color: rgb(74, 74, 74);\">Networking is a key for all 3 mentioned ARENAS:</strong></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(74, 74, 74);\">Networking with a positive broadminded successful people will make your mind set like them. So it is always recommended to stay away from pseudo narrow minded people and try to network with successful broad minded people. </span><span style=\"color: rgb(84, 84, 84);\">The people that you hang around with and talk to do influence who you are and what you do, so it is important to be surrounding yourself with positive, uplifting people that help you to grow and thrive your mind set.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(74, 74, 74);\">In our ARENA ‘Spending Habits’, we have spoken about investments and if you are really keen to learn best assets where your money could be invested, you will have to be in network of people who are successful investors. There are 1000’s of people selling 1000’s of investment opportunities, you need to act smart and be in network of people investing successfully. </span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(74, 74, 74);\">In our ARENA ‘Passive Income’, if you expect passive income opportunities to come walking to your door steps, you are still living in a dream world. Passive income and any other opportunity will come to your only if you surround yourself with wider network of positive people.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(74, 74, 74);\">Only fools go to buy gold in vegetable market. Smart people go to gold market to buy gold. So if you are looking for income opportunities, you will have to be among the network of people who are successful. You need to be in network of people who are either in Group A or on a path of people who are committed enough to move in that direction.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(74, 74, 74);\">Networking is also very useful in generating referrals and increased business. One of the best ways to do this is by joining networking activities and networking groups. Referrals that you get through networking are normally high quality and most of the time are pre-qualified for you. </span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(74, 74, 74);\">Networking with good business owners brings an abundance of opportunities! Opportunities like joint ventures, client leads, partnerships, speaking and writing opportunities, business or asset sales;and the list goes on. The opportunities within networking are endless. </span><span style=\"color: rgb(84, 84, 84);\">Just make sure you are jumping on board with the right opportunities and don’t go jumping into every opportunity that comes your way. The opportunities that you get involved in should align with your goals/vision, otherwise you might find that you are spinning your wheels chasing opportunity and getting nowhere.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(84, 84, 84);\">“It’s not WHAT you know, but WHO you know”. This is so true in business.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(84, 84, 84);\">Networking provides you with a great source of connections and opens the door to talk to highly influential people that you wouldn’t otherwise be able to easily talk or find. It’s not just about who you are networking with– as that person might already have other networks you can tap into. So ask the right questions to find out if the person you are networking with knows who you want to know!</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(84, 84, 84);\">Networking is a great way to tap into advice and expertise that you wouldn’t otherwise be able to get hold of. Just make sure you are getting solid advice from the right person – someone that actually knows about what you need to know and not from someone who is just giving you their opinion on something that they have no or very little experience in.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(84, 84, 84);\">Networking is actually an art and could be learned with some practise. Most of the people are shy talking to other people and it requires some amount of practise to break the ice. It is recommended never to sell when you talk to someone for the first time. People from Group A normally have hobbies like reading, playing golf, charities, polo etc and if possible, you can join these activities where you can get a lot of chances to network with these people. You can share your goals, hobbies, aspirations and other similarities during your first meet and gradually start talking business. Networking groups, Religious gatherings, family functions, Seminars and webinars are few of the best ways to network quickly with positive groups.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(84, 84, 84);\">Facebook and other digital platforms have made networking so easy and people can connect so quickly.</span></p><p><strong style=\"color: rgb(84, 84, 84);\"><u>To summarise-</u></strong></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">We have referred 10 % of population which owns 86% of world’s wealth as Group A&amp; 90 % of population which owns 14% of world’s wealth as Group B. To reach from Group B to Group A, one has to:</span></p><ul><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Change their mind set from narrow, fixed &amp; negative to big, positive &amp; broad. </strong></li><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Change spending pattern from spending unnecessarily to spending on assets (investment)</strong></li><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Don’t rely only on active income and start looking for sources of passive income</strong></li><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Expand your network of positive people.</strong></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">The video you have seen till now is just a trailer, if you are really keen to expertise each arena, you can join our community. There are 2 memberships we are offering:</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">General Membership: Joining fees INR 1000 for lifetime</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In general membership you will become our lifelong member</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;You can watch all our videos step by step through our software and can thus start your journey towards financial abundance</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We see that we guide our members in a best possible way to attain financial freedom and start earning passive income</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Core Membership: Joining fees INR 10000 for lifetime</span></p><ul><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">As a core member you will be integral part of our management committee</strong></li><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Core members will be given access to watch all videos step by step through our software and can thus start journey towards financial abundance</strong></li><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Core members will be asked to join our regular webinars</strong></li><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Core members will be asked to join our regular meetings</strong></li><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Core members can refer any person to become our core member and will earn 25% of membership fees as a reference fees</strong></li><li><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Eg – If Rekha has joined as a core member and referring Rakhi to join our community as a core member than Rekha will earn INR 2500/- as a reference fees.</span></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Core members will be entitled to earn regular passive income as 25% of any new joinee as a core member will be shared equally among all the core members. </span></p><ul><li><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Eg – If there are 10 core members in our community and Ajay is joining as an eleventh member than INR 2500/- will be shared even among all the core members before joining of Ajay i.e. each core member will earn INR 250 as a passive income without doing anything.</span></li><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Any earning opportunity arise within our community will be discussed with core members. </strong></li><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Core members can network with other core members within our community </strong></li><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Who are we?</strong></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">We are GPM Community involved and focused on to teach financial literacy among masses with an aim to create awareness on financial mistakes people do. We have been researching on financial literacy subject since last 10 years and accordingly come up with a concrete Plan Of Action (POA) which can help anyone to upscale his financial class. We have designed step by step processes to move towards Group A which are practical and easy to implement. We work towards all four ARENA’s simultaneously which will:</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Make your mind lot positive and start thinking like people in Group A</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Make you clever in your spending habits but giving detailed knowledge on financial literacy</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Give opportunity to earn passive income</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Give opportunity to network with like minded people</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">We have tried to cover 4 parameters which an individual can work on to move towards group A. It’s not a one day or a one-week activity but a regular workout which can move any person towards Group A. Lets present yourself or your loved ones a chance to move towards financial abundance by joining our community. </span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Kindly click given link to join our community</span></p>',4,'2019-01-03 13:18:34','2018-12-29 19:13:15');
